1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,756
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:02,756 --> 00:00:04,976
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,976 --> 00:00:08,926
Five people with sharp romance radars
have gathered.

4
00:00:08,926 --> 00:00:11,076
[The panel of five people is here]

5
00:00:11,076 --> 00:00:14,276
We learned the tenants' ages
and occupations last week.

6
00:00:14,276 --> 00:00:17,166
They used to be like, "Wow, he's a model."

7
00:00:17,166 --> 00:00:19,286
"Wow. He's a doctor."

8
00:00:19,286 --> 00:00:22,516
But now, they're like, "23? 25?"

9
00:00:22,516 --> 00:00:27,026
The occupations don't matter.
The ages caused chaos.

10
00:00:27,026 --> 00:00:29,136
Yes, to the tenants, too.

11
00:00:29,136 --> 00:00:33,336
Park Wu Yeol, a 25-year-old marketer.

12
00:00:33,336 --> 00:00:37,816
- Did you expect that?
- Wouldn't he stand out too much at work?

13
00:00:37,816 --> 00:00:39,486
- I thought it fit him.
- Me, too.

14
00:00:39,486 --> 00:00:42,176
- Working in Seongsu-dong fit him, too.
- Really?

15
00:00:42,176 --> 00:00:45,886
A lot of them know what's trendy right now.

16
00:00:45,886 --> 00:00:48,166
But he stands out too much. He's 188 cm tall.

17
00:00:48,166 --> 00:00:51,006
True, but based on his personality,

18
00:00:51,006 --> 00:00:54,136
I don't think he has good work relationships.

19
00:00:54,136 --> 00:00:57,306
Why? Why would you go that far?

20
00:00:57,306 --> 00:00:59,756
That's a bias against good-looking people.

21
00:00:59,756 --> 00:01:01,346
"They don't get along with people."

22
00:01:01,346 --> 00:01:03,076
"He must have a flaw."

23
00:01:03,076 --> 00:01:05,726
Whenever I see tall young men like him,

24
00:01:05,726 --> 00:01:07,706
I think, "Isn't that uncomfortable?"

25
00:01:07,706 --> 00:01:09,036
[LOL]

26
00:01:09,036 --> 00:01:11,736
- That's what I think.
- Feel too much gravity.

27
00:01:11,736 --> 00:01:14,626
- 170 cm is perfect.
- It's perfect.

28
00:01:14,626 --> 00:01:18,866
We thought Kim Seo Won was
an engineer or a science major.

29
00:01:18,866 --> 00:01:20,486
I had no idea he was a model.

30
00:01:20,486 --> 00:01:25,836
You didn't think he'd be a model
since he looks so much like one.

31
00:01:25,836 --> 00:01:29,066
The most unexpected one was Kang Yu Gyeong.

32
00:01:29,066 --> 00:01:31,406
- She's a college student.
- The youngest.

33
00:01:31,406 --> 00:01:33,756
We even thought she was the oldest female.

34
00:01:33,756 --> 00:01:36,856
- I thought she was the oldest.
- I thought so, too.

35
00:01:36,856 --> 00:01:38,276
And Kim Seong Min.

36
00:01:38,276 --> 00:01:39,986
- We guessed correctly.
- He's a doctor.

37
00:01:39,986 --> 00:01:41,936
The way he washed his hands.

38
00:01:41,936 --> 00:01:44,176
- Who washes their hands like that?
- I know.

39
00:01:44,176 --> 00:01:46,856
And Jeong Gyu Ri.

40
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:49,506
She makes hanbok.
She's a hanbok brand director.

41
00:01:49,506 --> 00:01:52,256
She's 29, born in '98.

42
00:01:52,256 --> 00:01:56,396
She's very competent and commanding at work.

43
00:01:56,396 --> 00:01:58,926
Her job must be tough.

44
00:01:58,926 --> 00:02:00,776
And lastly, Kim Min Ju.

45
00:02:00,776 --> 00:02:03,026
A marketer. We thought she was the youngest.

46
00:02:03,026 --> 00:02:04,846
Right. She looked the youngest.

47
00:02:04,846 --> 00:02:10,606
Her demeanor totally changes
when she's in and out of work.

48
00:02:10,606 --> 00:02:12,406
And another highlight.

49
00:02:12,406 --> 00:02:14,906
A male game-changer arrived on Day 2.

50
00:02:14,906 --> 00:02:17,966
He came in full speed. Jeong Jun Hyeon.

51
00:02:17,966 --> 00:02:19,226
Jun Hyeon.

52
00:02:19,226 --> 00:02:21,966
He's a criminal lawyer.
He works criminal cases.

53
00:02:21,966 --> 00:02:24,466
He's a masculine type you see in movies.

54
00:02:24,466 --> 00:02:27,866
He really looked like a manly type.

55
00:02:27,866 --> 00:02:31,426
If someone like him shows
a soft side, you fall in love.

56
00:02:31,426 --> 00:02:34,766
It drives you crazy. Totally.

57
00:02:34,766 --> 00:02:37,636
Which one do you find most difficult to read?

58
00:02:37,636 --> 00:02:40,756
- Wu Yeol is too naughty.
- Naughty?

59
00:02:40,756 --> 00:02:43,776
He said nice things to Gyu Ri in the morning.

60
00:02:43,776 --> 00:02:45,646
I thought they were it that day.

61
00:02:45,646 --> 00:02:49,026
But he flirted with Yu Gyeong in the evening.

62
00:02:49,026 --> 00:02:50,866
What are you doing right now?

63
00:02:50,866 --> 00:02:52,436
He's angry.

64
00:02:52,436 --> 00:02:56,996
We tend to show
our true feelings more at night.

65
00:02:56,996 --> 00:02:59,596
- That's true.
- But he was truer in the morning.

66
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,936
And he changed as Jun Hyeon came.

67
00:03:01,936 --> 00:03:05,466
Wu Yeol was more aggressive than I thought.

68
00:03:05,466 --> 00:03:07,226
He felt intimidated by him.

69
00:03:07,226 --> 00:03:10,126
He's older, and they just met,

70
00:03:10,126 --> 00:03:11,866
but he displayed his discomfort.

71
00:03:11,866 --> 00:03:15,546
If they were our age, they would've fought.

72
00:03:15,546 --> 00:03:20,036
I don't think
you'd play mind games like that.

73
00:03:20,036 --> 00:03:23,556
- I attack without being direct.
- Oh, right.

74
00:03:23,556 --> 00:03:26,836
[The sun hasn't risen yet]

75
00:03:28,176 --> 00:03:31,306
- Six in the morning?
- Why is he up so early?

76
00:03:33,336 --> 00:03:36,876
Tomorrow's and Sunday's schedules
are the same.

77
00:03:36,876 --> 00:03:39,916
- Tomorrow, too? 6:30?
- Tomorrow and the day after.

78
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:41,076
[Seo Won is working this whole weekend]

79
00:03:41,076 --> 00:03:44,296
I have a rehearsal tomorrow, too.
I have to go early.

80
00:03:44,296 --> 00:03:46,666
He must have shows back-to-back.

81
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:51,816
[Going to work alone at dawn]

82
00:04:01,956 --> 00:04:06,686
[Signal House's first weekend]

83
00:04:07,466 --> 00:04:09,136
[Stretching]

84
00:04:09,136 --> 00:04:11,266
Is she stretching?

85
00:04:11,266 --> 00:04:13,766
- It's Min Ju.
- She's cute.

86
00:04:13,766 --> 00:04:19,766
[Relieving the stress by stretching]

87
00:04:20,276 --> 00:04:21,586
[Opening]

88
00:04:21,586 --> 00:04:23,316
Seong Min is airing out the house.

89
00:04:23,316 --> 00:04:26,356
[Seong Min is in the living room]

90
00:04:26,356 --> 00:04:28,426
He woke up early.

91
00:04:31,806 --> 00:04:34,066
[Zoom]

92
00:04:38,956 --> 00:04:42,566
[Starting the day feeling relaxed]

93
00:04:46,746 --> 00:04:48,366
[Heading to the kitchen]

94
00:04:48,366 --> 00:04:49,776
Is he cooking?

95
00:04:49,776 --> 00:04:52,776
[Starting to make breakfast]

96
00:04:53,746 --> 00:04:54,946
Gyu Ri.

97
00:04:54,946 --> 00:04:56,856
[Jeong Gyu Ri is up]

98
00:04:57,886 --> 00:05:00,116
- Huh?
- They're the same age.

99
00:05:00,116 --> 00:05:01,376
What are you doing?

100
00:05:01,376 --> 00:05:03,946
- I'm thinking of making something.
- Breakfast?

101
00:05:03,946 --> 00:05:08,066
- Should we cook together?
- It's too late for breakfast.

102
00:05:08,066 --> 00:05:10,981
- I made rice. I'm thinking kimchi fried rice.
- Sounds good.

103
00:05:10,981 --> 00:05:14,991
- They're on cooking duty today.
- Could you cut the kimchi?

104
00:05:15,896 --> 00:05:18,356
- Gosh.
- I knew... Are you okay?

105
00:05:18,356 --> 00:05:19,586
[Embarrassed]

106
00:05:19,586 --> 00:05:22,036
[Kimchi juice splattered on her face]

107
00:05:22,036 --> 00:05:24,366
It splattered on a funny spot.

108
00:05:24,366 --> 00:05:26,806
- She got juice on her face.
- Here you go.

109
00:05:26,806 --> 00:05:28,806
Thank you.

110
00:05:28,806 --> 00:05:31,126
I'll wipe it off here.

111
00:05:31,126 --> 00:05:33,586
I need to go to the bathroom.

112
00:05:34,586 --> 00:05:36,506
It's too funny.

113
00:05:39,236 --> 00:05:41,556
Huh? Who's that?

114
00:05:41,556 --> 00:05:44,756
I got a missed call at 10:30.
This is Park Wu Yeol.

115
00:05:44,756 --> 00:05:47,016
- Oh, my God.
- Yes, that's correct.

116
00:05:47,766 --> 00:05:51,426
Really? There must be one person.

117
00:05:55,846 --> 00:05:56,736
[Checking]

118
00:05:56,736 --> 00:06:00,316
- She's going the extra mile.
- She wants to impress him.

119
00:06:00,316 --> 00:06:02,746
[Hyper conscious
due to the unexpected encounter]

120
00:06:02,746 --> 00:06:04,496
Wow.

121
00:06:06,216 --> 00:06:09,866
- When did you get up?
- Me? Around 9:30?

122
00:06:09,866 --> 00:06:11,376
When did you get up?

123
00:06:11,376 --> 00:06:13,526
I got up just now.

124
00:06:13,526 --> 00:06:15,266
9:30...

125
00:06:15,266 --> 00:06:17,666
They chose each other last time.

126
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:21,076
- It smells pretty good...
- I know.

127
00:06:21,076 --> 00:06:24,616
Is it scallion oil? It smells so good.

128
00:06:24,616 --> 00:06:29,336
I feel like a chef, cooking like this.

129
00:06:29,336 --> 00:06:32,776
- Since I've got two pots going.
- Seong Min must be pretty good.

130
00:06:32,776 --> 00:06:35,836
- Will you make eggs?
- I'd love eggs.

131
00:06:35,836 --> 00:06:38,116
- Can I call Wu Yeol?
- Of course.

132
00:06:38,116 --> 00:06:42,396
- To make eggs...
- I wondered where he was.

133
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,116
I should call him.

134
00:06:45,116 --> 00:06:47,926
Gyu Ri said she's never been
into younger men.

135
00:06:47,926 --> 00:06:50,136
- I know. We're just getting started.
- Pointless.

136
00:06:50,136 --> 00:06:54,046
She never met a younger man like him.

137
00:06:54,046 --> 00:06:55,466
- Did you take a shower?
- Yes.

138
00:06:55,466 --> 00:06:57,106
[Jun Hyeon is starting his morning, too]

139
00:06:57,106 --> 00:07:01,266
You're so diligent. I thought you
slept in on weekends.

140
00:07:03,706 --> 00:07:05,596
Wu Yeol.

141
00:07:05,596 --> 00:07:07,666
- Make eggs, please.
- Okay.

142
00:07:07,666 --> 00:07:09,616
How nice.

143
00:07:09,616 --> 00:07:11,216
Here he is.

144
00:07:12,026 --> 00:07:14,696
- Are you here to make eggs?
- Yes.

145
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:18,976
- I'll make eggs.
- Look at her smiling.

146
00:07:21,316 --> 00:07:24,566
- You're the chef now.
- She's so different with him.

147
00:07:25,586 --> 00:07:27,216
I'm in trouble.

148
00:07:28,016 --> 00:07:30,666
She keeps looking at him.

149
00:07:30,666 --> 00:07:32,446
Yu Gyeong.

150
00:07:32,446 --> 00:07:34,736
[Kang Yu Gyeong is up]

151
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:39,796
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

152
00:07:39,796 --> 00:07:41,726
- Yu Gyeong is here.
- The pressure is on.

153
00:07:41,726 --> 00:07:44,356
I made the rest, but whatever.

154
00:07:44,356 --> 00:07:47,666
They love to hang out this season.

155
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:48,936
[Looking]

156
00:07:48,936 --> 00:07:52,836
- Where's Min Ju? Getting ready?
- She's still upstairs.

157
00:07:56,136 --> 00:07:58,186
There was one egg.

158
00:07:59,236 --> 00:08:00,936
[Reading the room / Heading over]

159
00:08:01,836 --> 00:08:02,966
[Lurking]

160
00:08:03,926 --> 00:08:07,066
- Gyu Ri clearly...
- I know.

161
00:08:15,476 --> 00:08:18,106
The eggs are actually...

162
00:08:18,106 --> 00:08:21,046
- Focus.
- It's the most important part.

163
00:08:21,046 --> 00:08:22,646
Don't pressure me like that.

164
00:08:22,646 --> 00:08:25,346
I made everything else, but...

165
00:08:25,346 --> 00:08:28,116
How can you pressure me like this?

166
00:08:28,116 --> 00:08:32,556
Simple tasks are the hardest to pull off.

167
00:08:34,086 --> 00:08:37,666
- It's not a nonstick pan.
- It's hard.

168
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:39,306
I don't know about this.

169
00:08:40,606 --> 00:08:41,976
Too much pressure.

170
00:08:41,976 --> 00:08:43,316
[Tap, tap]

171
00:08:43,316 --> 00:08:47,306
- You're pulling off the hard task.
- Yes. I have to.

172
00:08:49,066 --> 00:08:52,276
They're in trouble right now.

173
00:08:52,276 --> 00:08:55,876
Those two ladies are...

174
00:08:55,876 --> 00:08:59,096
You made all of us breakfast.

175
00:08:59,096 --> 00:09:02,886
I got up, but had nothing to do.

176
00:09:05,316 --> 00:09:06,866
[Stepping back]

177
00:09:07,786 --> 00:09:12,686
[They're looking at Wu Yeol side by side]

178
00:09:13,506 --> 00:09:14,816
[Tension building up quietly]

179
00:09:14,816 --> 00:09:17,316
Where should I put them? A plate?

180
00:09:17,316 --> 00:09:19,606
Put them on the rice.

181
00:09:20,936 --> 00:09:22,986
[Tasty looking]

182
00:09:22,986 --> 00:09:26,466
- I like putting the lid on, too.
- They're like poached eggs.

183
00:09:26,466 --> 00:09:28,266
Yes. I like that style.

184
00:09:28,266 --> 00:09:30,326
Yu Gyeong is next to him.

185
00:09:31,286 --> 00:09:34,586
I need plenty of oil since the pan is small.

186
00:09:34,586 --> 00:09:38,926
Yu Gyeong thinks
Wu Yeol texted her right now.

187
00:09:38,926 --> 00:09:39,966
Right.

188
00:09:39,966 --> 00:09:42,856
- Looks like Yu Gyeong has no idea.
- Totally.

189
00:09:42,856 --> 00:09:46,906
She thinks it's her and Wu Yeol.

190
00:09:46,906 --> 00:09:49,086
[Staring]

191
00:09:49,946 --> 00:09:52,046
You're pressuring me.

192
00:09:52,046 --> 00:09:53,606
You know...

193
00:09:55,176 --> 00:09:58,576
you're a hard worker.
You'll do better this time.

194
00:09:59,776 --> 00:10:02,306
- Looking forward to it.
- Don't pressure me.

195
00:10:03,456 --> 00:10:06,836
Didn't I come a long way with this pan?

196
00:10:06,836 --> 00:10:09,386
You haven't done anything yet.

197
00:10:09,386 --> 00:10:13,306
I guess I wanted to hear your answer quickly.

198
00:10:13,306 --> 00:10:16,666
- You improved a lot.
- What do we do?

199
00:10:17,996 --> 00:10:20,636
She's just staring like a cat.

200
00:10:22,426 --> 00:10:25,666
- How do you like your eggs?
- How?

201
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:29,656
- To pair with this...
- We've got the Bermuda Triangle.

202
00:10:29,656 --> 00:10:32,586
Gyu Ri's the one who brought him.

203
00:10:32,586 --> 00:10:34,636
You know what's tasty.

204
00:10:34,636 --> 00:10:37,716
Do you sprinkle sesame seeds like that?

205
00:10:37,716 --> 00:10:42,396
- So upsetting.
- Yu Gyeong is doing what she wanted.

206
00:10:42,396 --> 00:10:44,076
[Toss]

207
00:10:44,076 --> 00:10:46,466
- This is complimentary.
- Let's eat, Yellow.

208
00:10:46,466 --> 00:10:49,426
- She called her Yellow just now?
- What?

209
00:10:50,586 --> 00:10:52,026
[Joking]

210
00:10:52,616 --> 00:10:54,436
What do you think?

211
00:10:54,436 --> 00:10:58,496
It's scorched. It'd be fun to scrape it off.

212
00:10:58,496 --> 00:11:00,876
Yellow is her nickname.

213
00:11:00,876 --> 00:11:04,236
- My God. Come on.
- What do we do?

214
00:11:04,236 --> 00:11:05,686
He teases people like that.

215
00:11:05,686 --> 00:11:07,986
Gyu Ri got hurt again, right?

216
00:11:07,986 --> 00:11:10,046
- Yes, first thing in the morning.
- It's so sad.

217
00:11:10,046 --> 00:11:13,006
- This keeps happening to her.
- I'm hurt, too.

218
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:16,686
She didn't know what to do.
She didn't look happy.

219
00:11:16,686 --> 00:11:21,526
But she knows that he texted her last night.

220
00:11:21,526 --> 00:11:23,546
- Right.
- Gyu Ri knows.

221
00:11:23,546 --> 00:11:26,886
He came because she called him over,

222
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:29,756
but he's having so much fun with Yu Gyeong.

223
00:11:29,756 --> 00:11:31,856
I couldn't talk to him, either.

224
00:11:31,856 --> 00:11:36,306
Wu Yeol doesn't show
who he likes in front of a group.

225
00:11:36,306 --> 00:11:37,346
I think so, too.

226
00:11:37,346 --> 00:11:40,986
If he likes Gyu Ri, he doesn't
talk to her in front of people.

227
00:11:40,986 --> 00:11:43,573
But he approaches her 1:1. That's his style.

228
00:11:43,573 --> 00:11:44,586
I agree.

229
00:11:44,586 --> 00:11:46,266
It sounds pretty clever, actually.

230
00:11:46,266 --> 00:11:48,456
That drives one crazy.

231
00:11:48,456 --> 00:11:51,356
- It's to toy with one's heart.
- I know.

232
00:11:51,356 --> 00:11:53,196
It looks so good.

233
00:11:53,196 --> 00:11:55,386
It turned out so well.

234
00:11:55,386 --> 00:11:57,396
- Thanks for the meal.
- Is this how it feels?

235
00:11:57,396 --> 00:12:01,336
- Nervous for people to try my food.
- Nervous, right?

236
00:12:02,326 --> 00:12:04,466
[A big bite]

237
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,566
- Tasty, right?
- Yes.

238
00:12:09,566 --> 00:12:11,376
- Is it okay?
- It's tasty.

239
00:12:11,376 --> 00:12:13,196
- Right?
- I'm glad.

240
00:12:13,196 --> 00:12:16,346
Tastes like restaurant style.

241
00:12:16,346 --> 00:12:18,256
- The highest compliment from us.
- I know.

242
00:12:18,256 --> 00:12:21,236
- It tastes store-bought.
- It's in the freezer.

243
00:12:21,236 --> 00:12:23,216
- It's a meal kit.
- Just microwave it.

244
00:12:23,216 --> 00:12:24,766
They're cute.

245
00:12:26,636 --> 00:12:28,426
So good.

246
00:12:31,356 --> 00:12:35,086
- We finally have nice weather.
- I know.

247
00:12:35,086 --> 00:12:38,296
- I love the weekend.
- Me, too.

248
00:12:39,106 --> 00:12:42,166
I haven't felt this relaxed in a while.

249
00:12:42,166 --> 00:12:43,856
All office workers can agree.

250
00:12:43,856 --> 00:12:46,226
- Should we get some sun?
- We should go out.

251
00:12:46,226 --> 00:12:48,256
- The weather's so nice.
- Let's go out.

252
00:12:48,256 --> 00:12:52,176
Should we go to Yeongjongdo?
It's a nice drive, too.

253
00:12:52,176 --> 00:12:54,166
[First outing since they joined Signal House]

254
00:12:54,166 --> 00:12:56,956
- What do you think?
- So cute.

255
00:12:56,956 --> 00:12:58,006
[Goofy]

256
00:12:59,346 --> 00:13:00,266
So pretty.

257
00:13:00,266 --> 00:13:05,366
Should I dress like this or like this?

258
00:13:09,446 --> 00:13:10,986
[Tap, tap]

259
00:13:13,236 --> 00:13:16,786
[The men are feeling nervous, too]

260
00:13:16,786 --> 00:13:19,676
Gosh, he has nice skin.

261
00:13:19,676 --> 00:13:23,976
[Preparing to go out, feeling nervous]

262
00:13:25,756 --> 00:13:27,866
They must be excited.

263
00:13:32,736 --> 00:13:35,116
- Are we taking three cars?
- Should we?

264
00:13:35,116 --> 00:13:36,096
Sure.

265
00:13:36,096 --> 00:13:38,526
The three men will be driving.

266
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:41,616
Wait in the car. Take the passenger seat.

267
00:13:41,616 --> 00:13:43,826
The women are choosing randomly?

268
00:13:43,826 --> 00:13:45,236
Gyu Ri knows.

269
00:13:45,236 --> 00:13:48,906
Should we decide on the order to go out?

270
00:13:48,906 --> 00:13:50,466
Rock, paper, scissors?

271
00:13:50,466 --> 00:13:52,806
Rock, paper, scissors.

272
00:13:52,806 --> 00:13:54,996
Rock, paper, scissors.

273
00:13:54,996 --> 00:13:57,516
Wow, I keep losing.

274
00:13:57,516 --> 00:13:58,676
One, two, three?

275
00:13:58,676 --> 00:14:01,526
[Gyu Ri, Yu Gyeong, then Min Ju]

276
00:14:01,526 --> 00:14:03,956
I'll end up with the smallest car.

277
00:14:03,956 --> 00:14:07,106
You don't know. You don't know
what you're choosing.

278
00:14:07,106 --> 00:14:10,716
- It's relative.
- It's unpredictable because it's relative.

279
00:14:10,716 --> 00:14:13,126
[Gyu Ri is first. Which car will she choose?]

280
00:14:13,126 --> 00:14:15,976
She's lost in thought. She's so torn.

281
00:14:15,976 --> 00:14:17,566
She must've picked one already.

282
00:14:17,566 --> 00:14:19,606
It's supposed to be random,

283
00:14:19,606 --> 00:14:22,496
but one of them knows
which car one person has.

284
00:14:22,496 --> 00:14:25,546
- That's right.
- They drove to work together the other day.

285
00:14:25,546 --> 00:14:28,456
Gyu Ri knows what Wu Yeol's car is.

286
00:14:28,456 --> 00:14:32,826
She was defeated by Yu Gyeong this morning.

287
00:14:32,826 --> 00:14:34,996
Isn't it possible she won't choose him?

288
00:14:34,996 --> 00:14:39,046
It's unlikely based on what
happened this morning.

289
00:14:39,046 --> 00:14:41,486
That makes her want to choose him more.

290
00:14:41,486 --> 00:14:42,996
Because she was hurt?

291
00:14:42,996 --> 00:14:47,976
She'd want to spend time with him
to find out if he's interested in her.

292
00:14:47,976 --> 00:14:50,216
Face time. Face time.

293
00:14:50,216 --> 00:14:53,966
[The women are stepping out first]

294
00:14:53,966 --> 00:14:56,366
They're different colors.

295
00:14:56,366 --> 00:14:58,466
The biggest car is...

296
00:15:00,536 --> 00:15:02,826
I can choose first, right?

297
00:15:02,826 --> 00:15:05,366
- I'll choose this one.
- Sounds good.

298
00:15:06,236 --> 00:15:08,626
Can't they see me
if I'm sitting in the front?

299
00:15:08,626 --> 00:15:10,856
What do we do?

300
00:15:10,856 --> 00:15:13,046
Without hesitation...

301
00:15:14,936 --> 00:15:18,216
[Gyu Ri chooses the car in the way back]

302
00:15:18,216 --> 00:15:20,236
The one in the back. That's Wu Yeol's.

303
00:15:20,236 --> 00:15:22,736
- The one she's getting in?
- Really?

304
00:15:22,736 --> 00:15:25,956
She knows. Why?
Why choose the one in the back?

305
00:15:25,956 --> 00:15:29,966
Right. She ran toward it too quickly.

306
00:15:29,966 --> 00:15:32,836
I think I like this one.

307
00:15:33,836 --> 00:15:38,006
[Yu Gyeong and Min Ju chose their cars]

308
00:15:42,286 --> 00:15:43,146
[Excited]

309
00:15:43,146 --> 00:15:44,146
This is so exciting.

310
00:15:44,146 --> 00:15:47,656
[Waiting while taking a deep breath]

311
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:51,016
[Ears perked]

312
00:15:51,016 --> 00:15:52,396
Is that your car?

313
00:15:52,396 --> 00:15:54,326
I'm curious.

314
00:15:55,876 --> 00:15:57,356
The front... This one.

315
00:15:57,356 --> 00:15:59,166
The one in the front?

316
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:03,956
- It was the big one. It was.
- Nice.

317
00:16:03,956 --> 00:16:07,056
- Get in.
- I have no idea.

318
00:16:08,556 --> 00:16:10,706
This is my car.

319
00:16:10,706 --> 00:16:12,746
- I had that feeling.
- Really?

320
00:16:12,746 --> 00:16:15,026
I got that feeling somehow.

321
00:16:15,026 --> 00:16:17,346
Really? Why?

322
00:16:17,346 --> 00:16:20,366
That's just the feeling I got.

323
00:16:20,366 --> 00:16:22,296
The heater was too hot.

324
00:16:22,296 --> 00:16:25,046
- I turned it off.
- Good job.

325
00:16:27,406 --> 00:16:29,606
- Can I play music?
- I'd love that.

326
00:16:29,606 --> 00:16:30,876
So cute.

327
00:16:30,876 --> 00:16:32,426
My gosh.

328
00:16:32,426 --> 00:16:35,146
I was listening to it earlier.

329
00:16:36,046 --> 00:16:40,206
[The music is giving them butterflies]

330
00:16:41,386 --> 00:16:43,996
[Checking]

331
00:16:48,806 --> 00:16:50,046
She's nervous.

332
00:16:50,046 --> 00:16:52,576
[Nervous for some reason]

333
00:16:52,576 --> 00:16:57,176
[Remembering that moment]

334
00:16:59,056 --> 00:17:00,726
[Staring]

335
00:17:00,726 --> 00:17:03,656
- I like that, too.
- They're like poached eggs.

336
00:17:03,656 --> 00:17:08,006
I like cooking with the lid on, too.
I like that style.

337
00:17:08,006 --> 00:17:12,996
[They're getting lost in thoughts]

338
00:17:13,536 --> 00:17:15,176
[Flinch]

339
00:17:15,176 --> 00:17:17,316
[Seong Min got the wrong car]

340
00:17:18,586 --> 00:17:20,196
He walked by.

341
00:17:20,196 --> 00:17:22,646
[Seong Min walks by]

342
00:17:22,646 --> 00:17:25,276
[There are two cars left]

343
00:17:27,776 --> 00:17:32,836
[Mumbling]

344
00:17:34,926 --> 00:17:36,616
Please.

345
00:17:36,616 --> 00:17:39,136
[Who's she waiting for?]

346
00:17:40,026 --> 00:17:41,496
Hello.

347
00:17:42,246 --> 00:17:44,496
Hello.

348
00:17:44,496 --> 00:17:46,386
[Smile]

349
00:17:49,296 --> 00:17:50,696
Wu Yeol?

350
00:17:50,696 --> 00:17:53,216
- She must be excited.
- I should take mine off, too.

351
00:17:53,216 --> 00:17:55,786
The coat, I mean.

352
00:18:02,406 --> 00:18:04,236
Everyone has a different car.

353
00:18:04,236 --> 00:18:06,706
Yes. They were all different.

354
00:18:07,536 --> 00:18:09,166
The car...

355
00:18:10,076 --> 00:18:11,536
[Flinching]

356
00:18:11,536 --> 00:18:13,676
Why did you choose this one?

357
00:18:14,796 --> 00:18:16,786
- Did you go first?
- Yes.

358
00:18:16,786 --> 00:18:18,616
Because it's cute?

359
00:18:21,456 --> 00:18:24,636
Wow, did you see him asking?
"Why did you choose this car?"

360
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:26,776
- "Did you go first?"
- She's been in that car.

361
00:18:26,776 --> 00:18:29,756
He's so forward when they're alone.

362
00:18:29,756 --> 00:18:31,636
He's driving the older women crazy.

363
00:18:31,636 --> 00:18:34,636
You really are, buddy.

364
00:18:35,496 --> 00:18:36,456
[Hehehe]

365
00:18:37,376 --> 00:18:39,786
- No.
- Is that so?

366
00:18:41,336 --> 00:18:42,966
What?

367
00:18:45,866 --> 00:18:48,526
Did you know it was my car?

368
00:18:48,526 --> 00:18:50,046
Yes.

369
00:18:53,146 --> 00:18:54,286
It's warm, isn't it?

370
00:18:54,286 --> 00:18:56,296
Yes. Let's turn it off.

371
00:18:57,936 --> 00:18:59,876
Anything you'd like to eat there?

372
00:18:59,876 --> 00:19:01,736
Don't you know?

373
00:19:03,636 --> 00:19:05,836
- Sashimi?
- Yes.

374
00:19:10,276 --> 00:19:13,266
- I knew his car.
- Right.

375
00:19:13,266 --> 00:19:17,526
I knew which one was Wu Yeol's
since we carpooled once.

376
00:19:17,526 --> 00:19:19,446
I like the color of the car.

377
00:19:19,446 --> 00:19:20,906
I can choose first, right?

378
00:19:20,906 --> 00:19:24,226
They probably don't know that we carpooled.

379
00:19:24,226 --> 00:19:27,026
But I don't have to tell them.

380
00:19:27,026 --> 00:19:29,186
- Right.
- Of course not.

381
00:19:29,186 --> 00:19:31,746
[Driving together for the second time]

382
00:19:35,856 --> 00:19:38,936
[Glancing]

383
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:46,366
We know each other's age and occupation.

384
00:19:46,366 --> 00:19:49,136
Don't you think we can talk casually?

385
00:19:49,136 --> 00:19:52,256
No? Is it too soon?

386
00:19:52,256 --> 00:19:53,546
Too soon?

387
00:19:53,546 --> 00:19:57,136
But to be honest, I...

388
00:19:57,136 --> 00:19:58,996
[Looking]

389
00:19:59,756 --> 00:20:01,566
[Hesitating]

390
00:20:01,566 --> 00:20:05,926
- I'm not good at talking casually.
- No?

391
00:20:05,926 --> 00:20:13,996
I'm afraid I'll get too comfortable if I do.

392
00:20:13,996 --> 00:20:16,816
- It makes me...
- Worried?

393
00:20:16,816 --> 00:20:19,176
Yes. I tend to...

394
00:20:20,076 --> 00:20:23,686
prefer talking formally for a while.

395
00:20:23,686 --> 00:20:26,186
Okay. I'll accommodate you, then.

396
00:20:26,186 --> 00:20:28,106
Do you prefer talking casually?

397
00:20:28,106 --> 00:20:30,746
Not that I prefer it, but...

398
00:20:30,746 --> 00:20:32,326
I was just asking.

399
00:20:32,326 --> 00:20:35,336
I was curious about your style.

400
00:20:35,336 --> 00:20:38,756
She just told him how she feels.
She doesn't want to be friends.

401
00:20:38,756 --> 00:20:40,916
She did. She did.

402
00:20:42,016 --> 00:20:49,346
I talked formally with my exes, too.

403
00:20:49,346 --> 00:20:51,126
Oh, really?

404
00:20:54,516 --> 00:20:56,686
I think it's different when you...

405
00:20:56,686 --> 00:21:01,016
It feels very different
when you talk formally.

406
00:21:01,016 --> 00:21:04,926
The excitement lasts long.
You respect each other,

407
00:21:04,926 --> 00:21:08,826
and the relationship lasts longer, I think.

408
00:21:08,826 --> 00:21:11,576
Once you start talking casually,

409
00:21:11,576 --> 00:21:17,836
you feel comfortable and become like friends.

410
00:21:19,706 --> 00:21:21,746
Okay. I understand it now.

411
00:21:23,136 --> 00:21:24,696
They're good at communicating.

412
00:21:24,696 --> 00:21:26,856
[Looking around]

413
00:21:30,436 --> 00:21:33,926
- I like both.
- He's so cool.

414
00:21:33,926 --> 00:21:38,066
[While getting to know each other carefully]

415
00:21:38,066 --> 00:21:40,216
Can you not see?

416
00:21:41,546 --> 00:21:44,826
[Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong's car]

417
00:21:45,426 --> 00:21:47,236
It's puffy here.

418
00:21:47,236 --> 00:21:48,876
- You're right.
- Like an allergic reaction.

419
00:21:48,876 --> 00:21:51,316
Should be fine. It's itchy,

420
00:21:52,396 --> 00:21:54,426
- Here.
- I'll take a little.

421
00:21:54,426 --> 00:21:55,616
[Moisturizer]

422
00:22:01,006 --> 00:22:03,546
- Nice, right?
- Yes.

423
00:22:03,546 --> 00:22:06,676
I brought tons of snacks for us.

424
00:22:06,676 --> 00:22:08,056
[Bottomless snack pocket]

425
00:22:08,056 --> 00:22:10,536
- You brought so much.
- Right?

426
00:22:11,546 --> 00:22:13,386
Play your favorite song next.

427
00:22:13,386 --> 00:22:15,346
- We should get excited now.
- We do.

428
00:22:15,346 --> 00:22:17,476
- I'll pick the songs.
- Sounds good.

429
00:22:17,476 --> 00:22:20,136
So you can focus on driving.

430
00:22:22,286 --> 00:22:25,546
Day 1? HONNE? I love it.

431
00:22:29,676 --> 00:22:32,646
[Min Ju is pacing her emotions]

432
00:22:32,646 --> 00:22:37,486
I think I'll feel at home after
just a couple more days.

433
00:22:37,486 --> 00:22:40,336
To be honest,

434
00:22:40,336 --> 00:22:45,186
I've always thought I adjust
well to my environment.

435
00:22:45,186 --> 00:22:48,276
I've been good at adjusting to any situation.

436
00:22:48,276 --> 00:22:49,706
[Got one text on Day 2]

437
00:22:49,706 --> 00:22:52,166
[Tired Camel: I felt relaxed thanks to you]

438
00:22:52,166 --> 00:22:56,976
[That evening]

439
00:22:56,976 --> 00:22:59,116
We try to work hard together.

440
00:22:59,116 --> 00:23:00,016
[Staring]

441
00:23:02,676 --> 00:23:06,956
[He was looking at someone else]

442
00:23:10,896 --> 00:23:13,776
[Concerned]

443
00:23:14,436 --> 00:23:16,856
[Their hearts...]

444
00:23:16,856 --> 00:23:18,996
When someone's wearing a scent...

445
00:23:18,996 --> 00:23:22,776
[drift away from what they hoped for]

446
00:23:24,066 --> 00:23:30,486
[The moment hurt feelings
became more pronounced]

447
00:23:31,046 --> 00:23:33,396
[Tossing and turning]

448
00:23:33,396 --> 00:23:37,356
But I couldn't get used to it.
I couldn't sleep, either.

449
00:23:38,616 --> 00:23:40,296
Oh...

450
00:23:41,686 --> 00:23:44,916
That's why I write every day.

451
00:23:44,916 --> 00:23:47,386
I think all men here do.

452
00:23:47,386 --> 00:23:50,296
I describe the situation first.

453
00:23:50,296 --> 00:23:52,686
My feelings. Feeling this way or that.

454
00:23:52,686 --> 00:23:56,686
- Whether I fell in love instantly.
- Right, right.

455
00:23:58,456 --> 00:24:01,426
I've always fallen in love instantly.

456
00:24:01,426 --> 00:24:03,776
I've been in relationships like that.

457
00:24:03,776 --> 00:24:06,776
- But I don't want that anymore.
- Really?

458
00:24:06,776 --> 00:24:09,526
I'm trying to control my feelings

459
00:24:09,526 --> 00:24:13,006
when I instantly fall for someone.

460
00:24:13,006 --> 00:24:15,126
But I'm not so sure.

461
00:24:18,336 --> 00:24:22,606
I suppress my feelings when I feel that way.

462
00:24:22,606 --> 00:24:24,526
I suppress it first.

463
00:24:24,526 --> 00:24:34,036
Because I don't know if it's just
excitement or something deeper.

464
00:24:34,036 --> 00:24:36,206
I'm too cautious.

465
00:24:38,396 --> 00:24:44,586
But I think that's just my personality.

466
00:24:46,296 --> 00:24:48,276
I see.

467
00:24:48,276 --> 00:24:50,126
So, you fall instantly...

468
00:24:51,836 --> 00:24:54,676
I don't want to, either.

469
00:24:54,676 --> 00:24:58,016
What's important? The first impression or...

470
00:24:58,926 --> 00:25:01,686
[Thinking]

471
00:25:02,636 --> 00:25:04,986
I'm really curious about it.

472
00:25:04,986 --> 00:25:07,036
First impression?

473
00:25:07,036 --> 00:25:09,706
[Remembering Seong Min's first impression]

474
00:25:09,706 --> 00:25:12,386
His eyes are very pure, too.

475
00:25:12,386 --> 00:25:15,936
I thought I could develop feelings for him.

476
00:25:15,936 --> 00:25:20,006
- Like, your feelings?
- I'm afraid I'll tell you everything.

477
00:25:20,006 --> 00:25:23,296
- Okay, okay.
- I'm not good at being strategic.

478
00:25:23,296 --> 00:25:24,796
Okay, okay. I got it.

479
00:25:24,796 --> 00:25:29,816
- Don't ask questions that are too direct.
- Okay, okay.

480
00:25:29,816 --> 00:25:32,186
Then, I'll learn everything about you

481
00:25:32,186 --> 00:25:36,256
- and write it all down tonight.
- Min Ju's current state.

482
00:25:36,256 --> 00:25:38,956
- This is how she is.
- This is her.

483
00:25:44,466 --> 00:25:46,226
Interesting...

484
00:25:52,606 --> 00:25:58,636
[Trying to stop feelings from escaping]

485
00:25:58,636 --> 00:26:00,946
[Meanwhile]

486
00:26:00,946 --> 00:26:03,856
[Sparkling]

487
00:26:03,856 --> 00:26:05,866
Are you hot? A little, right?

488
00:26:05,866 --> 00:26:07,586
I think I am a little.

489
00:26:07,586 --> 00:26:10,976
- Should I roll down the windows?
- Sounds good.

490
00:26:10,976 --> 00:26:12,226
[Hair flopping]

491
00:26:12,226 --> 00:26:13,486
- Put it up?
- Sorry, sorry.

492
00:26:13,486 --> 00:26:15,626
It's okay. It's okay.

493
00:26:15,626 --> 00:26:18,086
I didn't know it was so windy.

494
00:26:20,896 --> 00:26:22,876
Should I open the back ones, then?

495
00:26:22,876 --> 00:26:24,656
That's a good idea, too.

496
00:26:24,656 --> 00:26:27,736
Gosh. He's so attentive.

497
00:26:27,736 --> 00:26:29,766
[Checking]

498
00:26:29,766 --> 00:26:32,766
I don't like checking the mirror often.

499
00:26:32,766 --> 00:26:34,126
You don't like that?

500
00:26:34,126 --> 00:26:36,596
- No, I don't.
- Why?

501
00:26:36,596 --> 00:26:38,406
Makes me look like a princess.

502
00:26:38,406 --> 00:26:42,316
I don't want people to think that about me.

503
00:26:42,316 --> 00:26:44,486
It's nice to check often.

504
00:26:45,486 --> 00:26:47,156
They're cute.

505
00:26:49,726 --> 00:26:53,396
[A boy who grew up too quickly]

506
00:26:53,396 --> 00:26:56,086
What did you major in?

507
00:26:56,086 --> 00:26:57,736
Can you guess?

508
00:26:57,736 --> 00:26:59,456
Physical education?

509
00:26:59,456 --> 00:27:02,756
I studied aerospace engineering.

510
00:27:02,756 --> 00:27:03,986
- Wow.
- So crazy.

511
00:27:03,986 --> 00:27:06,276
Unexpected, right?

512
00:27:06,276 --> 00:27:08,756
Were you in that field?

513
00:27:08,756 --> 00:27:12,176
No, I joined the army while in the program.

514
00:27:12,176 --> 00:27:15,826
I studied to transfer after being discharged.

515
00:27:15,826 --> 00:27:20,166
Since I lived alone, I had to make money.

516
00:27:20,166 --> 00:27:23,326
But I came across a good opportunity.

517
00:27:23,326 --> 00:27:27,756
That's how I've been working
for this company for two years.

518
00:27:28,976 --> 00:27:32,456
- I'm planning to stay there for now.
- Keep at it?

519
00:27:34,966 --> 00:27:37,486
Is there something you'd
like to do in the future?

520
00:27:37,486 --> 00:27:39,946
In the future? To be honest,

521
00:27:39,946 --> 00:27:45,236
I get influenced by new experiences.

522
00:27:45,236 --> 00:27:48,336
- So, I keep changing.
- Yes.

523
00:27:49,026 --> 00:27:52,636
But since the CEO is an entrepreneur,

524
00:27:52,636 --> 00:27:54,706
I get affected by that, too.

525
00:27:54,706 --> 00:27:56,106
- That's right.
- I can see that.

526
00:27:56,106 --> 00:27:59,246
[They think about the future
a lot at their age]

527
00:28:00,506 --> 00:28:05,326
But I've been feeling rushed
more than I thought.

528
00:28:05,326 --> 00:28:09,726
So, I've been feeling anxious a lot.

529
00:28:09,726 --> 00:28:11,626
About the phase I'm in.

530
00:28:11,626 --> 00:28:17,516
But I changed my mindset a lot recently.

531
00:28:17,516 --> 00:28:19,756
Now, I'm just...

532
00:28:21,726 --> 00:28:25,616
- I'm just giving my best each day.
- So cool.

533
00:28:26,546 --> 00:28:30,306
You realized it very quickly.

534
00:28:30,306 --> 00:28:34,446
Really? I've spent a lot of time alone.

535
00:28:34,446 --> 00:28:38,606
I didn't have friends around me
once I left home.

536
00:28:38,606 --> 00:28:42,986
All of my friends were somewhere else.

537
00:28:42,986 --> 00:28:45,756
I've been alone
and had a lot of time to think.

538
00:28:45,756 --> 00:28:49,426
I came to be realistic naturally.

539
00:28:52,806 --> 00:28:54,466
Unexpected, right?

540
00:28:54,466 --> 00:28:56,556
No.

541
00:28:56,556 --> 00:28:59,966
- I assumed you were like that.
- Really?

542
00:29:00,966 --> 00:29:04,196
I could tell you think a lot.

543
00:29:04,196 --> 00:29:06,906
Thinking a lot can be good,

544
00:29:06,906 --> 00:29:10,166
- but it's hard a lot of times.
- Right. I know.

545
00:29:10,166 --> 00:29:14,046
- You seem thoughtful, too.
- Yes, I am, too.

546
00:29:15,486 --> 00:29:18,786
You realize it was nothing later.

547
00:29:20,286 --> 00:29:24,196
Worrying about something
doesn't mean it will happen.

548
00:29:24,196 --> 00:29:25,806
Right.

549
00:29:27,676 --> 00:29:29,706
[The night of the move-in day]

550
00:29:29,706 --> 00:29:31,536
Did you spill something?

551
00:29:31,536 --> 00:29:33,406
I just noticed it.

552
00:29:34,416 --> 00:29:36,846
I should eat gracefully.

553
00:29:36,846 --> 00:29:39,106
You didn't eat much.

554
00:29:39,106 --> 00:29:41,676
Me? I know.

555
00:29:41,676 --> 00:29:46,426
I think I'm still a bit nervous.

556
00:29:47,926 --> 00:29:50,476
We didn't reveal the information yesterday.

557
00:29:50,476 --> 00:29:51,876
I think that was nice.

558
00:29:51,876 --> 00:29:56,726
If someone's mature, that image sticks.

559
00:29:57,976 --> 00:30:00,366
Did they give us this lint roller?

560
00:30:00,366 --> 00:30:05,926
Wu Yeol picked those up
on the way home today.

561
00:30:05,926 --> 00:30:08,016
Shower heads, too.

562
00:30:10,706 --> 00:30:12,736
Do you want a latte today, too?

563
00:30:12,736 --> 00:30:13,746
[Laughs]

564
00:30:13,746 --> 00:30:14,956
Yes.

565
00:30:14,956 --> 00:30:17,476
- Vanilla?
- Yes.

566
00:30:18,426 --> 00:30:19,676
[Leaning]

567
00:30:19,676 --> 00:30:23,896
I noticed how sweet he is.

568
00:30:23,896 --> 00:30:25,776
- See you.
- Bye.

569
00:30:26,676 --> 00:30:30,576
I learned that age isn't important.

570
00:30:30,576 --> 00:30:33,626
- Wu Yeol is pretty mature.
- He is.

571
00:30:34,466 --> 00:30:38,416
[Thinking]

572
00:30:38,416 --> 00:30:43,776
[He's young, but mature]

573
00:30:47,346 --> 00:30:50,176
[Glancing]

574
00:30:50,176 --> 00:30:52,806
Isn't it time to apply the lip balm?

575
00:30:52,806 --> 00:30:55,146
I've been applying.

576
00:30:56,776 --> 00:30:58,926
[Tap, tap]

577
00:31:04,066 --> 00:31:07,086
[Checking]

578
00:31:14,976 --> 00:31:16,896
Do you like neutral tones?

579
00:31:16,896 --> 00:31:20,516
I think I buy a lot of neutral tones.

580
00:31:20,516 --> 00:31:22,836
I have brown ones, too.

581
00:31:24,036 --> 00:31:26,306
- I'll show them to you later.
- What?

582
00:31:26,306 --> 00:31:28,456
That sounds nice.

583
00:31:30,166 --> 00:31:32,366
[A bus is passing them]

584
00:31:32,366 --> 00:31:35,506
You're a good driver.

585
00:31:35,506 --> 00:31:38,426
- Do you feel comfortable?
- I usually...

586
00:31:38,426 --> 00:31:42,756
get scared when cars pass.

587
00:31:42,756 --> 00:31:45,896
I get scared when I see things like that.

588
00:31:45,896 --> 00:31:48,876
- You know what I mean, right?
- I do.

589
00:31:48,876 --> 00:31:53,126
I didn't think about cars all this time.

590
00:31:53,126 --> 00:31:56,686
- Driving skills are important.
- Right, right.

591
00:31:58,086 --> 00:32:01,076
When it comes to people,

592
00:32:01,076 --> 00:32:04,216
do you observe them for a long time

593
00:32:04,216 --> 00:32:08,096
or can you read them immediately?

594
00:32:08,096 --> 00:32:11,736
I can get a sense after meeting
about three times.

595
00:32:13,036 --> 00:32:16,586
I don't get to know them too deeply

596
00:32:16,586 --> 00:32:19,446
- but everyone has certain qualities.
- Yes.

597
00:32:19,446 --> 00:32:25,946
I can get a sense
when I notice those qualities.

598
00:32:27,786 --> 00:32:30,236
How long do you observe people?

599
00:32:30,236 --> 00:32:32,206
Well...

600
00:32:34,336 --> 00:32:37,986
- Six months?
- No, no.

601
00:32:37,986 --> 00:32:40,156
Well...

602
00:32:40,156 --> 00:32:41,866
A month, to be honest.

603
00:32:41,866 --> 00:32:43,706
- A month?
- Yes.

604
00:32:47,446 --> 00:32:48,806
Look at the ocean.

605
00:32:48,806 --> 00:32:52,396
[Almost reaching the ocean]

606
00:32:52,396 --> 00:32:53,726
I'm curious about these two.

607
00:32:53,726 --> 00:32:57,306
They're in totally different fields.
A lawyer and a dancer.

608
00:32:57,306 --> 00:32:59,576
[Yum]

609
00:33:00,576 --> 00:33:01,666
It's good.

610
00:33:01,666 --> 00:33:04,096
Right? I like this, too.

611
00:33:07,366 --> 00:33:09,076
The bears...

612
00:33:09,076 --> 00:33:12,296
- The basic kind?
- Yes, I usually get those.

613
00:33:12,296 --> 00:33:14,716
- Yes.
- There was a name for it.

614
00:33:14,716 --> 00:33:17,576
[An hour and a half ago]

615
00:33:17,576 --> 00:33:20,416
[Right before leaving]

616
00:33:25,576 --> 00:33:27,316
- Hello.
- Hello.

617
00:33:27,316 --> 00:33:29,296
- I didn't know this was my car.
- Really?

618
00:33:29,296 --> 00:33:32,956
- You drove this once.
- I drove it briefly at night.

619
00:33:32,956 --> 00:33:33,936
[Gummy bears]

620
00:33:33,936 --> 00:33:36,146
He must carry that around.

621
00:33:36,146 --> 00:33:37,756
[Glancing]

622
00:33:41,116 --> 00:33:44,356
I've only driven one car my whole life.

623
00:33:44,356 --> 00:33:47,276
So, it's a bit... I warned you.

624
00:33:47,276 --> 00:33:49,646
[Joking]

625
00:33:50,316 --> 00:33:51,466
- Really?
- Yes.

626
00:33:51,466 --> 00:33:53,236
I trust you. I will.

627
00:33:53,236 --> 00:33:55,536
[A nerve-racking start]

628
00:33:58,636 --> 00:34:01,746
[Gummy bears and The Black Skirts]

629
00:34:02,386 --> 00:34:06,896
- I heard you sleep a lot.
- Yes, I sleep well.

630
00:34:09,016 --> 00:34:15,206
When I'm free, I sometimes wake up around 1.

631
00:34:15,206 --> 00:34:18,136
I like to sleep in.

632
00:34:28,416 --> 00:34:31,106
I've never used CarPlay.

633
00:34:31,106 --> 00:34:33,846
I'll try with my phone.

634
00:34:33,846 --> 00:34:35,596
- Gosh.
- That's nice.

635
00:34:35,596 --> 00:34:37,826
Could you do this for me?

636
00:34:37,826 --> 00:34:38,866
[Embarrassed]

637
00:34:38,866 --> 00:34:41,406
Gosh, my song...

638
00:34:41,406 --> 00:34:44,916
"1:05." That's my favorite song. I mean it.

639
00:34:45,936 --> 00:34:50,216
The song she played accidentally
is his favorite.

640
00:34:50,216 --> 00:34:52,426
Is that true, or is he lying?

641
00:34:54,386 --> 00:34:57,356
You're definitely an ISFP.

642
00:34:58,856 --> 00:35:02,686
I've been listening to
The Black Skirts a lot lately.

643
00:35:07,146 --> 00:35:09,716
- Of all songs, it's "1:05."
- I know.

644
00:35:09,716 --> 00:35:12,866
I wasn't even listening to it.

645
00:35:18,026 --> 00:35:23,996
[The coincidence revealed
their common ground]

646
00:35:26,096 --> 00:35:27,706
So embarrassing.

647
00:35:38,146 --> 00:35:41,466
- You must like gummy bears.
- Yes, I like Haribo.

648
00:35:41,466 --> 00:35:45,036
- The lawyer likes gummy bears.
- Have some.

649
00:35:45,036 --> 00:35:46,556
I love gummy bears.

650
00:35:46,556 --> 00:35:48,976
Huh? Really?

651
00:35:48,976 --> 00:35:51,496
- I think you keep lying.
- I mean it.

652
00:35:51,496 --> 00:35:53,616
[Joking]

653
00:35:56,296 --> 00:35:59,216
I was shocked to hear you're an INFP.

654
00:35:59,216 --> 00:36:01,226
I don't look like it, right?

655
00:36:01,226 --> 00:36:03,336
You look...

656
00:36:05,256 --> 00:36:06,356
[Yum]

657
00:36:06,356 --> 00:36:09,476
People say it's bad
and I shouldn't reveal it.

658
00:36:09,476 --> 00:36:10,996
That you're an INFP?

659
00:36:10,996 --> 00:36:14,216
They say it's considered a bad one.

660
00:36:14,216 --> 00:36:17,816
I thought that a bit, too, because...

661
00:36:17,816 --> 00:36:21,846
INFPs have a unique sensibility.

662
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:23,796
Because we're reserved?

663
00:36:23,796 --> 00:36:26,446
And we think privately?

664
00:36:26,446 --> 00:36:29,946
I'm definitely a P.

665
00:36:29,946 --> 00:36:31,576
- Spontaneous?
- Yes.

666
00:36:31,576 --> 00:36:35,256
Even when I travel,
I'd randomly find good spots.

667
00:36:35,256 --> 00:36:38,986
- I prefer it that way.
- Right.

668
00:36:38,986 --> 00:36:41,386
I also...

669
00:36:41,386 --> 00:36:45,636
- Don't you walk a lot for that reason?
- I do.

670
00:36:45,636 --> 00:36:49,266
I kept walking. Like more than 10,000 steps.

671
00:36:49,266 --> 00:36:52,436
I walked a lot while listening to music.

672
00:36:52,436 --> 00:36:55,436
I repeated one song for several hours once.

673
00:36:55,436 --> 00:36:57,616
Me, too. I like repeating one song.

674
00:36:57,616 --> 00:36:59,926
They're connecting. They're connecting.

675
00:37:06,396 --> 00:37:08,246
I love this song.

676
00:37:09,246 --> 00:37:10,746
"Heya."

677
00:37:17,306 --> 00:37:20,326
- Honestly, I like being lazy, too.
- Really?

678
00:37:20,326 --> 00:37:23,886
- I can stay home for about a week.
- Really? Not go out at all?

679
00:37:23,886 --> 00:37:25,586
It's possible.

680
00:37:25,586 --> 00:37:28,916
She's so unusual. They're similar.

681
00:37:31,826 --> 00:37:39,266
[Someone likes the music I like]

682
00:37:48,836 --> 00:37:55,496
Do you actually worry about
getting your heart broken?

683
00:37:55,496 --> 00:37:57,146
- Of course.
- Really?

684
00:37:57,146 --> 00:37:59,746
In what way, for example?

685
00:37:59,746 --> 00:38:03,506
I tend to quickly fall...

686
00:38:04,756 --> 00:38:06,836
- For someone?
- Yes.

687
00:38:06,836 --> 00:38:09,196
- I fall quickly.
- You fall quickly, but...

688
00:38:09,196 --> 00:38:11,336
Unrequited love...

689
00:38:11,336 --> 00:38:14,536
- Have you experienced it?
- Of course.

690
00:38:15,536 --> 00:38:20,976
You can't apply the trauma
you experienced with

691
00:38:20,976 --> 00:38:26,766
your ex in future relationships.

692
00:38:26,766 --> 00:38:29,556
Right. Everyone's different.

693
00:38:30,946 --> 00:38:33,386
I hope I have a good relationship.

694
00:38:33,386 --> 00:38:36,396
- I think you will.
- You think so?

695
00:38:38,136 --> 00:38:44,666
I tend to trust people easily. That's why...

696
00:38:44,666 --> 00:38:46,286
- I can see that.
- Yes.

697
00:38:46,286 --> 00:38:51,916
I feel betrayed and hurt from that, too.

698
00:38:51,916 --> 00:38:54,336
But still...

699
00:38:54,336 --> 00:38:57,286
- Will I sound too old-fashioned?
- No.

700
00:38:57,286 --> 00:39:03,336
In the end, you realize that people
who understand you stay with you.

701
00:39:03,336 --> 00:39:06,876
You might think, "I've been betrayed.
I've been hurt.

702
00:39:06,876 --> 00:39:09,936
I won't trust anyone anymore."
Although it doesn't last.

703
00:39:09,936 --> 00:39:17,496
But don't feel that way because you'll
end up with better people later.

704
00:39:18,496 --> 00:39:21,806
- Did I sound like an old man?
- Not at all.

705
00:39:22,696 --> 00:39:25,316
I choked up a bit just now.

706
00:39:27,286 --> 00:39:33,416
[The sun is setting already]

707
00:39:33,996 --> 00:39:35,646
- It's good.
- Right?

708
00:39:35,646 --> 00:39:39,126
"Ling Ling?" This is my second favorite.

709
00:39:39,126 --> 00:39:42,836
The next song is my second favorite.

710
00:39:42,836 --> 00:39:44,516
Looking forward to it.

711
00:39:44,516 --> 00:39:46,726
- Music is forming a bond.
- It's huge.

712
00:39:46,726 --> 00:39:48,656
It's a powerful thing.

713
00:39:49,956 --> 00:39:52,735
The bridge everyone was excited about, right?

714
00:39:52,735 --> 00:39:53,517
That's right.

715
00:39:53,517 --> 00:39:56,147
- Wow.
- What a pretty view.

716
00:39:56,876 --> 00:39:59,536
- Wow.
- A nice sunset, too.

717
00:39:59,536 --> 00:40:01,556
You brought your passport, right?

718
00:40:01,556 --> 00:40:02,976
I can't tell you.

719
00:40:02,976 --> 00:40:04,526
What?

720
00:40:05,816 --> 00:40:07,726
It's so pretty.

721
00:40:07,726 --> 00:40:09,836
It is pretty. So pretty.

722
00:40:09,836 --> 00:40:12,916
- The sun happens to be setting, too.
- I know.

723
00:40:12,916 --> 00:40:15,626
Looking at the view through the camera

724
00:40:15,626 --> 00:40:20,036
suddenly moved me for some reason.

725
00:40:21,386 --> 00:40:23,396
[Water is reflecting the sunset
before their eyes]

726
00:40:24,046 --> 00:40:25,156
Ideal type?

727
00:40:25,156 --> 00:40:28,816
Maybe someone with similar qualities.

728
00:40:28,816 --> 00:40:33,366
- I think that's very important, too.
- Someone with similar qualities.

729
00:40:34,796 --> 00:40:37,606
The moon is up, too. Amazing.

730
00:40:37,606 --> 00:40:39,436
Come out.

731
00:40:39,436 --> 00:40:41,376
Come on out.

732
00:40:44,716 --> 00:40:47,036
- You're 29, Oppa?
- I'm 29.

733
00:40:47,036 --> 00:40:50,036
It's true. I'm pretty young.

734
00:40:51,636 --> 00:40:56,106
[What emotions will blossom next?]

735
00:40:56,106 --> 00:40:59,476
Daebak. A drive date.

736
00:40:59,476 --> 00:41:01,116
Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong.

737
00:41:01,116 --> 00:41:02,846
That was unusual.

738
00:41:02,846 --> 00:41:05,836
At first, you wonder, "Will these two work?"

739
00:41:05,836 --> 00:41:09,486
- Sharing the same taste in music is huge.
- Right.

740
00:41:09,486 --> 00:41:11,666
They're both "I"s in the MBTI, too.

741
00:41:11,666 --> 00:41:15,036
He said, "I think you will" earlier.

742
00:41:15,036 --> 00:41:17,736
- I think that choked her up.
- I know. It was like advice.

743
00:41:17,736 --> 00:41:20,556
That could be a tiny kindling.

744
00:41:20,556 --> 00:41:22,556
I can picture a romantic drama.

745
00:41:22,556 --> 00:41:26,946
Men around her age can't tell her that.

746
00:41:26,946 --> 00:41:33,426
That might've been when she fell
for an older man for the first time.

747
00:41:33,426 --> 00:41:34,916
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.

748
00:41:34,916 --> 00:41:36,996
Their conversation is...

749
00:41:36,996 --> 00:41:40,626
It feels mundane,
but they gel so well together.

750
00:41:40,626 --> 00:41:43,376
It continues to be that way.

751
00:41:43,376 --> 00:41:45,586
They wanted to see the ocean together, too.

752
00:41:45,586 --> 00:41:48,006
It's nice when it's just 1:1.

753
00:41:48,006 --> 00:41:50,436
But Wu Yeol changes in front of others.

754
00:41:50,436 --> 00:41:53,356
- Please.
- That draws her more.

755
00:41:53,356 --> 00:41:55,296
The six will get together again.

756
00:41:55,296 --> 00:41:57,646
I'm so curious how he'll behave later.

757
00:41:57,646 --> 00:41:59,376
Wu Yeol, seriously... I...

758
00:41:59,376 --> 00:42:00,596
[LOL]

759
00:42:00,596 --> 00:42:02,916
I'm older. I'm older than him.

760
00:42:02,916 --> 00:42:06,536
Keep it going with Gyu Ri when you arrive...

761
00:42:06,536 --> 00:42:09,196
I hope you continue talking to Gyu Ri.

762
00:42:09,196 --> 00:42:11,226
But if you switch to Yu Gyeong...

763
00:42:11,226 --> 00:42:13,046
Pull out a chair for Yu Gyeong.

764
00:42:13,046 --> 00:42:15,516
"Did you have a comfortable drive?"

765
00:42:15,516 --> 00:42:17,366
Let's not do that.

766
00:42:17,366 --> 00:42:19,036
[Getting too into it]

767
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:21,696
I'm so curious how he'll be
when they're all together.

768
00:42:21,696 --> 00:42:23,436
I'm dying to know.

769
00:42:23,436 --> 00:42:26,656
Thank you for the comfortable trip.

770
00:42:26,656 --> 00:42:27,756
They arrived.

771
00:42:27,756 --> 00:42:31,356
- This is a total seaside town.
- I know.

772
00:42:31,356 --> 00:42:34,466
- Go ahead.
- Thank you.

773
00:42:34,466 --> 00:42:36,416
Are we really first?

774
00:42:36,416 --> 00:42:38,566
We're here first.

775
00:42:38,566 --> 00:42:40,146
Look at this view.

776
00:42:40,146 --> 00:42:42,366
- Daebak.
- So nice.

777
00:42:42,366 --> 00:42:44,276
Wow, this is so nice.

778
00:42:44,276 --> 00:42:47,866
- I'm glad we got to catch the sunset.
- I know.

779
00:42:49,336 --> 00:42:50,516
I'm glad.

780
00:42:50,516 --> 00:42:51,906
- How about a photo?-
- Sounds good.

781
00:42:51,906 --> 00:42:53,466
Let's take one for each other.

782
00:42:53,466 --> 00:42:55,576
Are you good at taking portraits?

783
00:42:55,576 --> 00:42:58,556
I'm not a good model,
but I'm an okay photographer.

784
00:42:58,556 --> 00:43:01,056
- I might be okay.
- Take one of me.

785
00:43:01,056 --> 00:43:04,446
Maybe look over there naturally.

786
00:43:04,446 --> 00:43:06,866
- Take one from behind?
- Yes, could you...

787
00:43:06,866 --> 00:43:08,906
You're serious. I'm excited.

788
00:43:08,906 --> 00:43:11,326
I didn't think you'd take it so seriously.

789
00:43:11,326 --> 00:43:14,446
He's so attentive like that?

790
00:43:14,446 --> 00:43:15,986
Look over here.

791
00:43:15,986 --> 00:43:17,526
Min Ju is cute.

792
00:43:17,526 --> 00:43:18,466
[Click]

793
00:43:20,646 --> 00:43:23,786
[He's taking photos nonstop]

794
00:43:24,696 --> 00:43:28,076
[Passionate photographer]

795
00:43:28,076 --> 00:43:32,006
- Wow. You're good.
- You look like a troublemaker.

796
00:43:32,006 --> 00:43:34,426
- You're good.
- He took nice photos.

797
00:43:34,426 --> 00:43:38,136
- I'm not good at this stuff.
- Okay. I'll take care of it.

798
00:43:38,136 --> 00:43:42,096
It looks too much like an ID photo.

799
00:43:42,096 --> 00:43:45,366
- What should I do?
- Look over there.

800
00:43:45,366 --> 00:43:48,876
- I'll actually look.
- One, two, three. Oppa.

801
00:43:50,466 --> 00:43:52,486
- I got one.
- Is it okay?

802
00:43:52,486 --> 00:43:54,866
- Gosh.
- Looks nice, right?

803
00:43:54,866 --> 00:43:57,176
- I'm a good photographer.
- Yes.

804
00:43:57,176 --> 00:43:59,136
This is so natural.

805
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:00,636
- Should we take one together?
- Sure.

806
00:44:00,636 --> 00:44:03,666
They're the only couple
who are talking casually.

807
00:44:06,036 --> 00:44:07,726
[A cute selfie in front of the ocean]

808
00:44:07,726 --> 00:44:09,266
Looks nice. Nice lighting.

809
00:44:09,266 --> 00:44:11,936
I thought, "We really are like a couple."

810
00:44:11,936 --> 00:44:17,736
- We took a lot of photos today.
- We're dressed similar, too.

811
00:44:17,736 --> 00:44:19,646
Nice.

812
00:44:20,436 --> 00:44:22,886
It was already game over for me then.

813
00:44:22,886 --> 00:44:25,186
To be honest,

814
00:44:26,566 --> 00:44:27,906
I found the purpose.

815
00:44:27,906 --> 00:44:31,816
I found my purpose
for moving into Signal House.

816
00:44:31,816 --> 00:44:35,826
I met the one. I just need to move out now.

817
00:44:37,526 --> 00:44:39,326
- Really?
- So quick...

818
00:44:39,326 --> 00:44:41,546
She's already in love. What do we do?

819
00:44:41,546 --> 00:44:42,976
[This will be fun]

820
00:44:42,976 --> 00:44:44,696
Really?

821
00:44:44,696 --> 00:44:46,806
It's only been three days since we moved in.

822
00:44:46,806 --> 00:44:49,226
But it feels longer than that.

823
00:44:49,226 --> 00:44:51,556
Feels like it's been three weeks.

824
00:44:51,556 --> 00:44:53,796
- Can we start talking casually?
- Yes.

825
00:44:53,796 --> 00:44:55,856
- Should we start?
- Really? Okay.

826
00:44:55,856 --> 00:44:57,076
I'm good at it.

827
00:44:57,076 --> 00:45:00,056
- But you aren't doing it.
- I'm really good.

828
00:45:00,056 --> 00:45:04,136
The heart flutters instinctively,
but choose the one to love.

829
00:45:04,136 --> 00:45:10,846
We had both casual and candid
conversations so smoothly.

830
00:45:10,846 --> 00:45:12,676
- Surprising, right?
- Yeah, totally.

831
00:45:12,676 --> 00:45:18,286
We shared our feelings
very honestly while driving.

832
00:45:18,286 --> 00:45:20,596
It was harder than I expected.

833
00:45:20,596 --> 00:45:22,876
Act... Acting lightly...

834
00:45:22,876 --> 00:45:24,756
You don't act lightly at all.

835
00:45:24,756 --> 00:45:26,776
I always try to set the mood.

836
00:45:26,776 --> 00:45:28,516
That makes you look more serious.

837
00:45:28,516 --> 00:45:30,016
- Really?
- Yes.

838
00:45:30,016 --> 00:45:33,796
You're kind of
like a classical scholar, right?

839
00:45:33,796 --> 00:45:35,956
Just admit it.

840
00:45:35,956 --> 00:45:38,376
Don't people say you're a Confucius man?

841
00:45:38,376 --> 00:45:41,036
That's why I've always thought I was no fun.

842
00:45:41,036 --> 00:45:42,756
I thought we were so compatible.

843
00:45:42,756 --> 00:45:44,916
This is so fun. We're here.

844
00:45:44,916 --> 00:45:46,086
Min Ju is smitten.

845
00:45:46,086 --> 00:45:49,116
I felt so happy since then.

846
00:45:49,116 --> 00:45:51,466
I felt at ease since I didn't have to worry.

847
00:45:51,466 --> 00:45:52,906
- Right.
- Look at her.

848
00:45:52,906 --> 00:45:54,896
I wonder what others are talking about?

849
00:45:54,896 --> 00:45:57,196
- I wonder.
- What's taking them so long?

850
00:45:57,196 --> 00:46:00,556
Seong Min wonders about the others.

851
00:46:00,556 --> 00:46:02,346
[A perfectly timed laughter]

852
00:46:02,346 --> 00:46:04,086
Someone's coming.

853
00:46:04,086 --> 00:46:06,566
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri?

854
00:46:06,566 --> 00:46:08,006
It's not them.

855
00:46:08,006 --> 00:46:09,776
It was Yu Gyeong, of all people.

856
00:46:09,776 --> 00:46:12,766
- Gosh, you're so late.
- When did you get here?

857
00:46:12,766 --> 00:46:14,756
- Thirty minutes ago.
- Really?

858
00:46:14,756 --> 00:46:16,216
What took you so long?

859
00:46:16,216 --> 00:46:17,726
- Was there an accident?
- Pardon?

860
00:46:17,726 --> 00:46:20,826
His body is facing them now.

861
00:46:20,826 --> 00:46:22,756
Is this Wu Yeol?

862
00:46:22,756 --> 00:46:25,306
- Probably.
- I think so. They're here.

863
00:46:25,306 --> 00:46:28,446
What? We arrived around the same time.

864
00:46:28,446 --> 00:46:31,526
- Didn't we take the same route?
- I think so.

865
00:46:31,526 --> 00:46:33,966
You took a detour, right?

866
00:46:33,966 --> 00:46:36,836
It gave us the wrong route.

867
00:46:36,836 --> 00:46:38,696
Look at this. The sun is setting.

868
00:46:38,696 --> 00:46:40,976
It's so pretty.

869
00:46:40,976 --> 00:46:43,976
Good job driving all the way.

870
00:46:43,976 --> 00:46:46,446
- Aren't you hungry?
- I am.

871
00:46:46,446 --> 00:46:47,636
Let's get drinks.

872
00:46:47,636 --> 00:46:50,506
- I want an iced Americano.
- Me, too.

873
00:46:50,506 --> 00:46:51,926
Why is he looking at Yu Gyeong?

874
00:46:51,926 --> 00:46:53,756
[Flinching]

875
00:46:53,756 --> 00:46:55,806
Do they have a strawberry latte?

876
00:46:55,806 --> 00:46:57,306
Strawberry latte?

877
00:46:57,306 --> 00:46:59,696
- I'm sure they do.
- Probably.

878
00:46:59,696 --> 00:47:02,606
They have a cheese latte for sure.

879
00:47:02,606 --> 00:47:04,476
- For sure?
- I'm sure.

880
00:47:04,476 --> 00:47:07,196
I can say it definitively.

881
00:47:07,196 --> 00:47:09,186
I think so because...

882
00:47:09,186 --> 00:47:12,046
Cheese sounds too rich right now.

883
00:47:12,046 --> 00:47:14,986
Strawberry latte.

884
00:47:14,986 --> 00:47:16,836
The ocean looks so pretty.

885
00:47:16,836 --> 00:47:20,176
- What do we do?
- Nothing but ocean.

886
00:47:21,066 --> 00:47:23,166
I said I wanted to see the ocean yesterday.

887
00:47:23,166 --> 00:47:25,696
- Who did?
- Me.

888
00:47:25,696 --> 00:47:28,476
- Gyu Ri, too.
- This looks like a famous spot.

889
00:47:29,336 --> 00:47:31,736
We both wanted to see the ocean.

890
00:47:31,736 --> 00:47:34,486
I didn't think we'd see it today.

891
00:47:34,486 --> 00:47:36,306
"We both wanted to see the ocean."

892
00:47:36,306 --> 00:47:37,426
What a romantic thing to say.

893
00:47:37,426 --> 00:47:39,966
To a third person, it sounds like

894
00:47:39,966 --> 00:47:43,686
he's grouping them together. "We both."

895
00:47:43,686 --> 00:47:45,106
"We both."

896
00:47:45,866 --> 00:47:49,396
I didn't think we'd see it today.

897
00:47:49,396 --> 00:47:52,506
This is where dreams come true.

898
00:47:53,886 --> 00:47:56,496
What did you talk about on the way?

899
00:47:56,496 --> 00:47:59,836
- Well, just this and that.
- This and that.

900
00:47:59,836 --> 00:48:02,836
- Why are you so secretive?
- No, no.

901
00:48:02,836 --> 00:48:06,036
- They're talking with their eyes.
- "We talked more."

902
00:48:06,036 --> 00:48:08,386
What did you talk about, then?

903
00:48:08,386 --> 00:48:11,416
- We talked about every single thing.
- Really?

904
00:48:11,416 --> 00:48:14,266
- Could you give me an example?
- Example?

905
00:48:14,266 --> 00:48:16,156
Give us an extreme example.

906
00:48:16,156 --> 00:48:18,706
Extreme example?

907
00:48:19,576 --> 00:48:21,536
Which one should I choose?

908
00:48:21,536 --> 00:48:23,036
[Whoa]

909
00:48:23,556 --> 00:48:25,976
[Hehe]

910
00:48:26,696 --> 00:48:30,796
- Unexpectedly...
- We talked about music. Our taste in music.

911
00:48:30,796 --> 00:48:33,296
- Did you listen to music on the way?
- Yes.

912
00:48:33,296 --> 00:48:36,196
- We didn't listen to any music.
- Really?

913
00:48:36,196 --> 00:48:38,166
- No music at all?
- No.

914
00:48:38,166 --> 00:48:40,116
We just talked the whole time.

915
00:48:40,116 --> 00:48:42,056
Not listening to music is crazy.

916
00:48:42,056 --> 00:48:43,826
Yu Gyeong is bothered.

917
00:48:43,826 --> 00:48:46,516
But we thought...

918
00:48:47,676 --> 00:48:50,786
It was nice to focus on the conversation?

919
00:48:50,786 --> 00:48:52,916
We actually thought...

920
00:48:52,916 --> 00:48:55,676
There was no gap in the audio.

921
00:48:55,676 --> 00:48:58,176
What? Are they competing?

922
00:48:59,086 --> 00:49:01,556
Our audio overlapped.

923
00:49:01,556 --> 00:49:03,226
[Suddenly an audio competition]

924
00:49:03,226 --> 00:49:05,716
- Overlapped?
- "You go first."

925
00:49:07,726 --> 00:49:10,416
Do we have anything?

926
00:49:10,416 --> 00:49:13,666
You can't be triggered by stuff like this.

927
00:49:13,666 --> 00:49:16,786
- They were so smooth.
- It'd be weird to get triggered.

928
00:49:16,786 --> 00:49:19,336
Let's go as is.

929
00:49:19,336 --> 00:49:23,136
What would you like for dinner?
You all must be hungry.

930
00:49:23,136 --> 00:49:25,486
I wonder if Seo Won is off work.

931
00:49:25,486 --> 00:49:29,236
He'd be upset
if he heard we're in Yeongjongdo.

932
00:49:30,656 --> 00:49:32,326
Did you grab the Vaseline earlier?

933
00:49:32,326 --> 00:49:34,546
No... I have it.

934
00:49:34,546 --> 00:49:36,446
- Can I use it?
- Yes.

935
00:49:36,446 --> 00:49:39,036
Perfume yesterday, Vaseline tonight.

936
00:49:39,036 --> 00:49:41,296
- She's disappointed.
- She is.

937
00:49:41,296 --> 00:49:43,386
I left mine in the car.

938
00:49:43,386 --> 00:49:45,226
I never saw her make a face like that.

939
00:49:45,226 --> 00:49:48,536
Isn't this area known for grilled clams?

940
00:49:48,536 --> 00:49:51,506
[They're talking privately
in front of everyone]

941
00:49:51,506 --> 00:49:53,576
We're by the ocean now.

942
00:49:55,706 --> 00:49:59,906
- Yeongjongdo is quite far.
- He put it on his lips.

943
00:49:59,906 --> 00:50:01,536
[Sigh]

944
00:50:03,166 --> 00:50:05,236
Is she fuming?

945
00:50:05,236 --> 00:50:08,556
- I can tell she likes him a lot.
- She's like, "I can't be like this."

946
00:50:08,556 --> 00:50:13,836
He's toying with two women's hearts
without lifting a finger.

947
00:50:22,356 --> 00:50:26,316
[Someone is coming into the cafe]

948
00:50:27,256 --> 00:50:29,776
You all eat seafood, right?

949
00:50:29,776 --> 00:50:31,976
- Didn't you say you can't eat it?
- You don't like sashimi?

950
00:50:31,976 --> 00:50:34,366
I can eat it.

951
00:50:34,366 --> 00:50:35,646
- What?
- What?

952
00:50:35,646 --> 00:50:37,666
What?

953
00:50:37,666 --> 00:50:39,626
How did you get here?

954
00:50:39,626 --> 00:50:43,496
- You came.
- Should I grab a chair?

955
00:50:43,496 --> 00:50:45,756
What a relief.

956
00:50:45,756 --> 00:50:48,696
We just got here, too. How did you get here?

957
00:50:48,696 --> 00:50:51,126
It feels like I haven't seen him in a while.

958
00:50:51,126 --> 00:50:51,894
How awkward.

959
00:50:51,894 --> 00:50:54,546
Felt like this when you appeared last night.

960
00:50:54,546 --> 00:50:57,186
[Jun Hyeon's appearance shocked everyone]

961
00:50:57,186 --> 00:50:58,586
I think I get it.

962
00:50:58,586 --> 00:51:00,606
"What's he doing here?"

963
00:51:00,606 --> 00:51:02,296
How did you get here?

964
00:51:02,296 --> 00:51:05,466
- Me? I took a taxi.
- Seriously?

965
00:51:05,466 --> 00:51:07,426
Right after work.

966
00:51:07,426 --> 00:51:09,666
I'm glad you came.

967
00:51:09,666 --> 00:51:11,476
What did you do today?

968
00:51:12,476 --> 00:51:13,926
I'm not going to tell you.

969
00:51:13,926 --> 00:51:16,056
- You can check later.
- We had too much fun.

970
00:51:16,056 --> 00:51:18,566
A lot has happened.

971
00:51:18,566 --> 00:51:20,636
[Sad]

972
00:51:20,636 --> 00:51:22,916
[Joking]

973
00:51:22,916 --> 00:51:25,366
I'm jealous.

974
00:51:25,366 --> 00:51:27,976
- Don't feel too sad.
- Don't feel too sad.

975
00:51:27,976 --> 00:51:30,976
- We have food at home.
- We cooked, too.

976
00:51:30,976 --> 00:51:33,396
Dinner, too?

977
00:51:33,396 --> 00:51:36,886
We'll have dinner here.

978
00:51:36,886 --> 00:51:39,026
Looks like you became really tight.

979
00:51:39,026 --> 00:51:41,236
- Who?
- Jun Hyeon.

980
00:51:41,236 --> 00:51:43,856
I'm with him now.

981
00:51:43,856 --> 00:51:45,756
I'm sorry. I was...

982
00:51:45,756 --> 00:51:49,066
- He flirted so hard.
- I flirted with him.

983
00:51:49,066 --> 00:51:50,596
[Eyes closed]

984
00:51:51,716 --> 00:51:53,246
Already?

985
00:51:54,666 --> 00:51:57,206
He's mine on the weekends.

986
00:51:57,206 --> 00:52:00,446
Yu Gyeong is distracted right now.

987
00:52:01,436 --> 00:52:04,196
What brought you to Yeongjongdo?

988
00:52:04,196 --> 00:52:06,506
We wanted to have fun without you.

989
00:52:07,756 --> 00:52:10,416
Right next door? It is actually.

990
00:52:10,416 --> 00:52:12,286
- How should we sit?
- Like this?

991
00:52:12,286 --> 00:52:13,916
Four and three like this?

992
00:52:13,916 --> 00:52:17,466
- You want to put your coat away?
- I'm still cold.

993
00:52:17,466 --> 00:52:19,526
I'm so nervous.

994
00:52:19,526 --> 00:52:20,486
[Staring]

995
00:52:20,486 --> 00:52:22,956
A set?

996
00:52:22,956 --> 00:52:24,996
Shrimp and lobster?

997
00:52:24,996 --> 00:52:27,646
I like everything.

998
00:52:27,646 --> 00:52:29,226
Do you want this?

999
00:52:29,226 --> 00:52:31,786
Do you not have a menu?

1000
00:52:31,786 --> 00:52:34,436
- Can you eat a lot?
- Yes, I'm hungry.

1001
00:52:34,436 --> 00:52:36,836
Should we get four servings, then?

1002
00:52:36,836 --> 00:52:39,496
For each table...

1003
00:52:39,496 --> 00:52:45,296
I felt sick the whole time leaving the cafe.

1004
00:52:45,296 --> 00:52:48,696
I was feeling poorly.

1005
00:52:48,696 --> 00:52:50,656
I didn't feel good.

1006
00:52:51,936 --> 00:52:57,516
I'm not feeling so good right now.

1007
00:52:57,516 --> 00:53:00,326
I think the food will be served from here.

1008
00:53:00,326 --> 00:53:02,016
Could you sit here?

1009
00:53:02,826 --> 00:53:04,666
[Worried]

1010
00:53:06,826 --> 00:53:09,866
- I'm sorry.
- No, it's okay.

1011
00:53:09,866 --> 00:53:13,336
The three of us will get the lobster set B.

1012
00:53:13,336 --> 00:53:15,436
You get all this.

1013
00:53:16,656 --> 00:53:20,666
Are you hungry? Can we eat all of that?

1014
00:53:20,666 --> 00:53:23,536
I'm worried we can't finish it.

1015
00:53:23,536 --> 00:53:26,736
- What would you like?
- I don't care.

1016
00:53:26,736 --> 00:53:28,626
Because you can't eat?

1017
00:53:28,626 --> 00:53:31,486
- There's something in the back...
- Have a soda.

1018
00:53:31,486 --> 00:53:36,446
I don't think I can eat a lot right now.

1019
00:53:36,446 --> 00:53:38,956
Are you having indigestion?

1020
00:53:38,956 --> 00:53:41,416
I think it's car sickness.

1021
00:53:41,416 --> 00:53:44,386
- Are you car sick?
- I think so.

1022
00:53:44,386 --> 00:53:47,446
[Worried]

1023
00:53:47,446 --> 00:53:51,236
They might not have an emergency kit.
Is there a pharmacy...

1024
00:53:51,236 --> 00:53:54,406
- She looks pale right now.
- Something to keep you down.

1025
00:53:54,406 --> 00:53:56,806
She's really sick.

1026
00:53:56,806 --> 00:53:59,516
Don't you think there's
a convenience store nearby?

1027
00:53:59,516 --> 00:54:01,896
Why is he caring for her so much?

1028
00:54:01,896 --> 00:54:04,416
Huh? You'd better not go.

1029
00:54:05,446 --> 00:54:09,186
They might have emergency medicine here.

1030
00:54:10,836 --> 00:54:11,956
[Getting up]

1031
00:54:11,956 --> 00:54:14,786
- Gosh.
- Where is he going?

1032
00:54:15,776 --> 00:54:18,956
[Rummaging]

1033
00:54:22,216 --> 00:54:24,886
I'll stop by a convenience store.

1034
00:54:24,886 --> 00:54:27,216
- Where?
- Isn't there a convenience store?

1035
00:54:27,216 --> 00:54:28,906
[Surprised]

1036
00:54:28,906 --> 00:54:30,346
[Oh, no, Min Ju]

1037
00:54:30,346 --> 00:54:32,546
"Where?"

1038
00:54:32,546 --> 00:54:33,866
"Where?"

1039
00:54:33,866 --> 00:54:35,586
Min Ju can't hide her feelings.

1040
00:54:35,586 --> 00:54:37,646
It's a good reason, but...

1041
00:54:38,586 --> 00:54:40,636
You're going to a convenience store?

1042
00:54:40,636 --> 00:54:42,156
They probably have it.

1043
00:54:43,076 --> 00:54:47,046
[Everyone is stunned at
Seong Min's unexpected move]

1044
00:54:49,156 --> 00:54:52,366
- I'm so sorry.
- No, no. It's okay.

1045
00:54:52,366 --> 00:54:54,366
- It's nearby.
- Is it?

1046
00:54:55,326 --> 00:54:58,006
- I'll be right back.
- Should we go together, then?

1047
00:54:59,846 --> 00:55:02,356
It must bother her a lot.

1048
00:55:09,716 --> 00:55:11,176
I'm hungry.

1049
00:55:11,176 --> 00:55:15,156
It's inappropriate to say that now.
"I'm hungry."

1050
00:55:15,156 --> 00:55:17,156
She must be very sick.

1051
00:55:17,156 --> 00:55:20,796
She's feeling sick from the drive.

1052
00:55:20,796 --> 00:55:23,796
- Isn't it my fault?
- No.

1053
00:55:23,796 --> 00:55:27,366
I saw you passing us earlier.

1054
00:55:27,366 --> 00:55:29,256
Jun Hyeon drove her.

1055
00:55:29,256 --> 00:55:30,846
I think it's my fault.

1056
00:55:30,846 --> 00:55:32,426
[Sorry]

1057
00:55:32,426 --> 00:55:35,736
I feel so bad for Yu Gyeong.

1058
00:55:37,356 --> 00:55:41,796
- Which way do we go?
- Straight ahead from here.

1059
00:55:41,796 --> 00:55:43,066
Aren't you cold?

1060
00:55:43,066 --> 00:55:45,416
- I'm wearing a long coat.
- Let's walk slowly.

1061
00:55:45,416 --> 00:55:46,956
What a great chance.

1062
00:55:46,956 --> 00:55:50,836
- Let's get medicine if they have any.
- What should I take?

1063
00:55:50,836 --> 00:55:55,336
A digestive aid or a car sickness pill.

1064
00:55:55,336 --> 00:55:59,256
I think having sweets made it worse.

1065
00:55:59,256 --> 00:56:02,426
- Because you ate while feeling sick?
- The strawberry latte.

1066
00:56:02,426 --> 00:56:04,406
It was a bit rich.

1067
00:56:04,406 --> 00:56:08,276
I felt dizzy as we entered the restaurant.

1068
00:56:08,276 --> 00:56:11,546
It could've also been because
you stood up suddenly.

1069
00:56:11,546 --> 00:56:14,236
You were cooped up for a long time.

1070
00:56:14,236 --> 00:56:16,456
- Do you get this often?
- No.

1071
00:56:16,456 --> 00:56:19,096
You've never fainted from standing too long?

1072
00:56:19,096 --> 00:56:22,606
Standing too long? Not really.

1073
00:56:22,606 --> 00:56:25,536
If you take medicine
and get some fresh air...

1074
00:56:25,536 --> 00:56:29,546
Yes, I think I just need fresh air.

1075
00:56:29,546 --> 00:56:33,066
This is why you're a doctor.

1076
00:56:33,066 --> 00:56:35,036
Yes, sure.

1077
00:56:35,036 --> 00:56:38,066
- Thank you. I appreciate it.
- No problem.

1078
00:56:38,066 --> 00:56:43,986
[After the two left]

1079
00:56:43,986 --> 00:56:49,476
[Everyone suddenly got quiet]

1080
00:56:53,866 --> 00:56:57,246
How was driving with Jun Hyeon?

1081
00:56:57,246 --> 00:57:00,086
We haven't gotten a chance
to talk to him much.

1082
00:57:00,086 --> 00:57:02,136
- How our conversation was?
- Yes.

1083
00:57:02,136 --> 00:57:06,536
We have a lot in common.

1084
00:57:06,536 --> 00:57:09,536
For real. Our MBTI results are similar, too.

1085
00:57:09,536 --> 00:57:13,476
Not that. When I was talking to Min Ju,

1086
00:57:13,476 --> 00:57:16,726
- I was like, "You're lying" a lot.
- We were like that, too.

1087
00:57:16,726 --> 00:57:20,756
But we just kept joking around.

1088
00:57:20,756 --> 00:57:22,596
I know.

1089
00:57:22,596 --> 00:57:25,606
Who bought the sweet snacks?

1090
00:57:25,606 --> 00:57:27,436
- Why are you looking at me?
- It wasn't you?

1091
00:57:27,436 --> 00:57:30,756
- I did.
- You're so biased.

1092
00:57:30,756 --> 00:57:32,786
You judge people with prejudice.

1093
00:57:32,786 --> 00:57:35,226
Gosh, sorry.

1094
00:57:35,226 --> 00:57:36,896
[Hehe]

1095
00:57:36,896 --> 00:57:39,206
- What? What?
- It's nothing.

1096
00:57:39,206 --> 00:57:42,566
Aren't you smiling at me too much?

1097
00:57:42,566 --> 00:57:45,506
- I try hard to entertain people.
- Really?

1098
00:57:45,506 --> 00:57:48,676
Are you trying? You try hard.

1099
00:57:48,676 --> 00:57:51,966
- Talented.
- I'm a bit natural, too. It's both.

1100
00:57:51,966 --> 00:57:54,836
- I guess I wasn't funny just now.
- No.

1101
00:57:54,836 --> 00:57:58,056
- Keep at it, sir.
- I will.

1102
00:57:58,056 --> 00:58:00,006
He's different when he talks to Min Ju.

1103
00:58:00,006 --> 00:58:02,326
We weren't that harsh with him.

1104
00:58:02,326 --> 00:58:04,046
A little bit. A little bit.

1105
00:58:04,046 --> 00:58:06,316
- Did I do that?
- Yes.

1106
00:58:06,316 --> 00:58:08,476
- Often?
- Yes.

1107
00:58:09,376 --> 00:58:11,846
It's because I felt the impact.

1108
00:58:11,846 --> 00:58:14,796
Really? I think I heard about that.

1109
00:58:14,796 --> 00:58:16,526
I noticed I was getting a reaction.

1110
00:58:16,526 --> 00:58:19,176
[Laughing and walking with
Seong Min is making her feel better]

1111
00:58:19,176 --> 00:58:21,956
So, whenever I do something...

1112
00:58:24,036 --> 00:58:25,636
It's bigger than I thought.

1113
00:58:25,636 --> 00:58:27,256
I'm nervous.

1114
00:58:28,036 --> 00:58:32,716
Let's see if your prescription works.

1115
00:58:33,596 --> 00:58:36,406
Do you have a pharmacy section, sir?

1116
00:58:36,406 --> 00:58:38,646
No medicines? What a shame.

1117
00:58:38,646 --> 00:58:40,096
They don't have medicine.

1118
00:58:40,096 --> 00:58:41,696
What do I do?

1119
00:58:41,696 --> 00:58:44,356
- Should I take this?
- Maybe this instead.

1120
00:58:44,356 --> 00:58:46,886
A digestive drink prescribed by a doctor.

1121
00:58:46,886 --> 00:58:49,426
It might be a bit different.

1122
00:58:49,426 --> 00:58:51,686
The Beauty Digestive.

1123
00:58:51,686 --> 00:58:55,316
Here's your prescription.
The beauty recommends this.

1124
00:58:57,056 --> 00:58:58,366
Okay.

1125
00:58:58,366 --> 00:59:01,406
- Drink this right now.
- Thank you.

1126
00:59:01,406 --> 00:59:03,606
- It's for beauties.
- It is.

1127
00:59:03,606 --> 00:59:05,496
Thank you.

1128
00:59:06,436 --> 00:59:08,966
It's prescribed by a doctor.

1129
00:59:10,076 --> 00:59:11,926
They didn't have medicine.

1130
00:59:13,306 --> 00:59:18,616
I believe Seong Min knew that
they didn't have medicine there.

1131
00:59:18,616 --> 00:59:22,686
No, some of them sell it these days.

1132
00:59:22,686 --> 00:59:23,836
[Nice and hot]

1133
00:59:23,836 --> 00:59:26,266
[A delicious spread of seafood]

1134
00:59:26,266 --> 00:59:30,256
- I should serve you some.
- Let me do it.

1135
00:59:32,186 --> 00:59:33,256
[Mmm]

1136
00:59:33,256 --> 00:59:35,106
So good.

1137
00:59:35,106 --> 00:59:36,766
[Yum]

1138
00:59:39,966 --> 00:59:42,496
- She's so cute.
- Is it good?

1139
00:59:42,496 --> 00:59:44,666
[Nodding]

1140
00:59:44,666 --> 00:59:46,656
[Picking]

1141
00:59:48,086 --> 00:59:50,386
[Worried]

1142
00:59:51,456 --> 00:59:54,296
[The seat across from Min Ju is still empty]

1143
00:59:54,296 --> 00:59:56,416
They're taking too long.

1144
00:59:58,286 --> 00:59:59,336
[Tired]

1145
00:59:59,336 --> 01:00:01,746
She'll get indigestion now.

1146
01:00:02,666 --> 01:00:05,336
There are so many glasses.

1147
01:00:05,336 --> 01:00:08,366
- Should I make you a drink?
- Are you having some?

1148
01:00:08,366 --> 01:00:10,496
Soju cocktail.

1149
01:00:10,496 --> 01:00:11,926
Me, too.

1150
01:00:11,926 --> 01:00:15,976
How much soju? Should I measure with this?

1151
01:00:15,976 --> 01:00:19,786
Let's do it like this. Add enough.

1152
01:00:19,786 --> 01:00:21,836
- Is it too much?
- No.

1153
01:00:21,836 --> 01:00:24,146
- A little more?
- No, no, no.

1154
01:00:24,146 --> 01:00:27,106
It's a lot, but the first drink
should be strong.

1155
01:00:27,106 --> 01:00:29,476
I'll take half a glass.

1156
01:00:29,476 --> 01:00:31,326
Sorry.

1157
01:00:31,326 --> 01:00:32,696
Is this good?

1158
01:00:32,696 --> 01:00:35,416
- Too much? I'll give you a little.
- Okay.

1159
01:00:35,416 --> 01:00:38,306
You're asking her too much.

1160
01:00:38,306 --> 01:00:41,306
Everyone has a preference. This looks good.

1161
01:00:42,216 --> 01:00:44,406
I feel the pressure.

1162
01:00:46,606 --> 01:00:49,566
- Are you drinking?
- I'll drink soda.

1163
01:00:49,566 --> 01:00:52,266
Right. You can't drink.

1164
01:00:52,266 --> 01:00:55,596
- You drank a lot last night.
- I did.

1165
01:00:55,596 --> 01:00:59,436
- You turned red like your sweater.
- Seriously.

1166
01:00:59,436 --> 01:01:02,896
- I didn't feel good.
- I know.

1167
01:01:02,896 --> 01:01:04,986
I was really worried.

1168
01:01:04,986 --> 01:01:07,326
Seo Won is caring for her.

1169
01:01:07,326 --> 01:01:11,036
- You looked better after drinking water.
- I had to eat a lot, too.

1170
01:01:11,036 --> 01:01:15,766
[She keeps looking at the door]

1171
01:01:17,056 --> 01:01:19,436
[Concerned]

1172
01:01:21,036 --> 01:01:25,846
[Seong Min and Yu Gyeong
have been gone for a while]

1173
01:01:26,496 --> 01:01:27,846
How are you feeling now?

1174
01:01:27,846 --> 01:01:30,246
I feel better now.

1175
01:01:30,246 --> 01:01:32,616
I feel totally fine now.

1176
01:01:35,076 --> 01:01:38,546
We haven't talked this much before, have we?

1177
01:01:38,546 --> 01:01:40,896
No, except for the first day.

1178
01:01:40,896 --> 01:01:42,326
Right. The first day.

1179
01:01:42,326 --> 01:01:44,056
[They had a fun 1:1 conversation]

1180
01:01:44,056 --> 01:01:47,706
Right. We haven't since the first day.

1181
01:01:47,706 --> 01:01:51,656
We haven't had a chance to talk since then.

1182
01:01:51,656 --> 01:01:54,736
Right. We didn't.

1183
01:01:55,936 --> 01:01:59,306
But we got our chance now in a way.

1184
01:01:59,306 --> 01:02:01,896
- A chance?
- Don't you agree?

1185
01:02:03,846 --> 01:02:06,016
- Or not.
- No, no.

1186
01:02:06,016 --> 01:02:09,666
That didn't cross my mind at all.

1187
01:02:09,666 --> 01:02:12,416
I couldn't keep diagnosing you
the whole time.

1188
01:02:12,416 --> 01:02:15,806
How do you feel now?
Now? Do you feel better now?

1189
01:02:15,806 --> 01:02:18,336
I shouldn't feel bad
for talking to you, right?

1190
01:02:18,336 --> 01:02:20,916
No, no. I love it.

1191
01:02:20,916 --> 01:02:23,316
- Really?
- Of course.

1192
01:02:24,186 --> 01:02:26,396
It started feeling different since then.

1193
01:02:26,396 --> 01:02:28,656
That's how she felt.

1194
01:02:28,656 --> 01:02:31,736
Don't you want your hands in your pockets?

1195
01:02:31,736 --> 01:02:33,346
- It's because...
- Do you have something?

1196
01:02:33,346 --> 01:02:34,766
I don't have a hot pack.

1197
01:02:34,766 --> 01:02:36,736
- No, it's okay.
- I don't have one.

1198
01:02:36,736 --> 01:02:38,726
- Why was I doing this?
- I know.

1199
01:02:38,726 --> 01:02:40,256
I don't know, either.

1200
01:02:40,256 --> 01:02:43,226
- You were grateful.
- Yes, that's it.

1201
01:02:43,226 --> 01:02:47,106
"Thank you for healing me." Like that.

1202
01:02:47,976 --> 01:02:50,296
Do you like... Watch your head.

1203
01:02:50,296 --> 01:02:51,896
Gosh.

1204
01:02:51,896 --> 01:02:53,946
Be careful.

1205
01:02:53,946 --> 01:02:56,196
He's so different than when he's with Min Ju.

1206
01:02:56,196 --> 01:02:57,746
Totally different.

1207
01:02:57,746 --> 01:02:59,796
Are you feeling better? A lot better?

1208
01:02:59,796 --> 01:03:02,406
Yes. A lot better. Thank you so much.

1209
01:03:02,406 --> 01:03:04,226
It's thanks to the Beauty Digestive.

1210
01:03:04,226 --> 01:03:07,426
It was a perfect remedy for me.

1211
01:03:07,426 --> 01:03:08,866
It was perfect, right?

1212
01:03:08,866 --> 01:03:11,306
- Am I a good doctor?
- You are. Incredible.

1213
01:03:11,306 --> 01:03:13,266
- Let's go.
- Thank you.

1214
01:03:13,266 --> 01:03:18,526
[Yu Gyeong is healed, thanks
to Seong Min's treatment]

1215
01:03:18,526 --> 01:03:22,506
Seong Min is totally different than
when he's chatting with Min Ju.

1216
01:03:22,506 --> 01:03:24,836
The role switched completely.

1217
01:03:24,836 --> 01:03:28,276
He was playing Min Ju's role just now.

1218
01:03:28,276 --> 01:03:32,686
He got talkative and kept
trying to make her laugh.

1219
01:03:32,686 --> 01:03:35,346
I didn't know he was so good at flirting.

1220
01:03:35,346 --> 01:03:38,116
He gave her the Beauty Digestive.

1221
01:03:39,066 --> 01:03:41,116
She's been treated.

1222
01:03:41,116 --> 01:03:42,406
Are you okay?

1223
01:03:42,406 --> 01:03:44,976
- I feel better after getting fresh air.
- That's good.

1224
01:03:44,976 --> 01:03:47,746
- You probably won't drink.
- Jun Hyeon...

1225
01:03:47,746 --> 01:03:50,296
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

1226
01:03:52,026 --> 01:03:54,156
Was the convenience store far from here?

1227
01:03:54,156 --> 01:03:55,746
It's close by.

1228
01:03:55,746 --> 01:03:57,516
She's asking why it took so long.

1229
01:03:57,516 --> 01:03:59,916
Eat some. You haven't eaten at all.

1230
01:03:59,916 --> 01:04:01,266
Thanks for the meal.

1231
01:04:01,266 --> 01:04:05,396
- Wow, so much food.
- I'll serve you right away.

1232
01:04:05,396 --> 01:04:06,836
He's a bit much.

1233
01:04:06,836 --> 01:04:09,736
- Seo Won.
- What's with his face?

1234
01:04:09,736 --> 01:04:12,846
[Everyone is taking photos]

1235
01:04:13,886 --> 01:04:17,176
- You're a good photographer.
- Am I?

1236
01:04:17,176 --> 01:04:19,666
Should I show you mine?

1237
01:04:19,666 --> 01:04:21,776
This is what I took earlier.

1238
01:04:21,776 --> 01:04:24,596
She's so upset right now.

1239
01:04:24,596 --> 01:04:26,486
Everyone's in the frame.

1240
01:04:27,346 --> 01:04:29,396
Is this no good?

1241
01:04:29,396 --> 01:04:32,556
Is it no good? Memories. It's funny.

1242
01:04:32,556 --> 01:04:35,306
What? What are you looking at?

1243
01:04:36,876 --> 01:04:38,786
It's just for our memories.

1244
01:04:38,786 --> 01:04:42,006
- He basically ignored her.
- Food photos.

1245
01:04:43,826 --> 01:04:46,936
- That's brutal.
- It's just for me.

1246
01:04:46,936 --> 01:04:49,966
- I won't show it to anyone.
- She's in a bad mood.

1247
01:04:49,966 --> 01:04:51,606
We can eat this.

1248
01:04:52,456 --> 01:04:54,356
Have some.

1249
01:04:54,356 --> 01:04:57,276
- Right, seafood...
- Do you want this instead?

1250
01:04:57,276 --> 01:04:58,796
[Worried]

1251
01:04:58,796 --> 01:05:01,976
- Ramen.
- Eat this instead of raw food.

1252
01:05:01,976 --> 01:05:05,616
- Ramen.
- I'll eat slowly.

1253
01:05:05,616 --> 01:05:08,076
I'll eat sashimi, then.

1254
01:05:09,086 --> 01:05:12,066
When she said that, her eyes were...

1255
01:05:12,066 --> 01:05:13,276
[Sparkly]

1256
01:05:13,276 --> 01:05:14,626
Sparkly eyes.

1257
01:05:14,626 --> 01:05:17,306
On the way here,

1258
01:05:17,306 --> 01:05:20,786
she kept talking about sashimi and soju.

1259
01:05:20,786 --> 01:05:22,576
There's still a lot left.

1260
01:05:22,576 --> 01:05:25,136
- I know.
- It's complicated for everyone.

1261
01:05:25,136 --> 01:05:29,536
Sir, are the clams cooked? Thank you.

1262
01:05:30,536 --> 01:05:31,646
Should we have a drink?

1263
01:05:31,646 --> 01:05:33,616
Yes, sounds good.

1264
01:05:33,616 --> 01:05:35,596
Let me join you.

1265
01:05:36,596 --> 01:05:38,226
Should we drink together?

1266
01:05:39,226 --> 01:05:42,746
Join us. You're making us sad.

1267
01:05:42,746 --> 01:05:44,606
Should I order another soda?

1268
01:05:44,606 --> 01:05:46,986
I think I'm good.

1269
01:05:46,986 --> 01:05:48,406
That means no?

1270
01:05:48,406 --> 01:05:50,246
- No.
- Okay.

1271
01:05:51,436 --> 01:05:54,556
I haven't had food like this that many times.

1272
01:05:54,556 --> 01:05:57,006
I'm not that crazy about stuff like this.

1273
01:05:57,006 --> 01:06:01,226
- I think I'd find it memorable.
- What's this now?

1274
01:06:01,226 --> 01:06:03,246
What percentage are you at?

1275
01:06:03,246 --> 01:06:05,466
He's looking out for Gyu Ri.

1276
01:06:05,466 --> 01:06:07,136
0%.

1277
01:06:07,136 --> 01:06:11,386
[Wu Yeol only has eyes for Gyu Ri]

1278
01:06:11,386 --> 01:06:13,536
You should talk more.

1279
01:06:14,536 --> 01:06:19,436
I wanted to see you slightly buzzed.

1280
01:06:19,436 --> 01:06:22,706
- He wants to see her drunk.
- Not at all.

1281
01:06:22,706 --> 01:06:26,546
He's 100% flirting by saying that.

1282
01:06:26,546 --> 01:06:28,556
You're resisting getting drunk?

1283
01:06:28,556 --> 01:06:31,586
I'm totally sober.

1284
01:06:31,586 --> 01:06:35,026
She's in trouble.
She's getting rejected again.

1285
01:06:37,516 --> 01:06:39,426
Are you still feeling sick?

1286
01:06:39,426 --> 01:06:42,636
I feel okay here, but not here.

1287
01:06:42,636 --> 01:06:45,536
- It's her head now.
- Where? Head?

1288
01:06:45,536 --> 01:06:47,876
Gosh, that's enough.

1289
01:06:47,876 --> 01:06:49,826
He's a doctor.

1290
01:06:49,826 --> 01:06:52,636
About seven channels are going on.

1291
01:06:52,636 --> 01:06:54,356
Seriously, that's...

1292
01:06:54,356 --> 01:06:57,576
- Each belongs to a different station.
- They're all different.

1293
01:06:57,576 --> 01:06:59,186
Where? Head?

1294
01:06:59,186 --> 01:07:03,076
I feel a lot better here now.
I felt out of it earlier...

1295
01:07:03,076 --> 01:07:05,156
I'm not sick anymore.

1296
01:07:06,546 --> 01:07:07,786
We went there and...

1297
01:07:07,786 --> 01:07:12,516
Sometimes convenience stores
have pharmacy stuff.

1298
01:07:12,516 --> 01:07:14,616
But they didn't have any.

1299
01:07:14,616 --> 01:07:19,486
I just became a normal person.
I had nothing to do.

1300
01:07:19,486 --> 01:07:21,556
My gosh.

1301
01:07:21,556 --> 01:07:24,006
- Continue the story.
- What?

1302
01:07:24,006 --> 01:07:26,906
What kind of finish is that?

1303
01:07:27,836 --> 01:07:30,136
I took a digestive aid.

1304
01:07:30,136 --> 01:07:34,796
It was called the Beauty Digestive.

1305
01:07:34,796 --> 01:07:37,236
There was one called the Beauty Digestive.

1306
01:07:37,236 --> 01:07:40,986
- He prescribed that to me.
- Oh, my God.

1307
01:07:40,986 --> 01:07:45,406
How sweet. Incredibly sweet.
What a sweet doctor.

1308
01:07:45,406 --> 01:07:46,736
Look at her expression.

1309
01:07:46,736 --> 01:07:50,166
I'm a T, but I acted like an F.

1310
01:07:51,316 --> 01:07:53,836
I was mad at Seong Min.

1311
01:07:53,836 --> 01:07:58,466
I learned how he expresses his interest.

1312
01:07:58,466 --> 01:08:01,226
- He didn't say that to her.
- I know.

1313
01:08:01,226 --> 01:08:03,536
[Chatty]

1314
01:08:03,536 --> 01:08:06,416
When I heard the word "Beauty,"

1315
01:08:06,416 --> 01:08:09,636
I thought it was a perfect
expression of his feelings.

1316
01:08:09,636 --> 01:08:12,806
"It's Yu Gyeong."
That's when I first realized that.

1317
01:08:12,806 --> 01:08:14,246
Min Ju is quick.

1318
01:08:14,246 --> 01:08:16,896
She's better off knowing that.

1319
01:08:19,056 --> 01:08:20,736
Is there something you want from here?

1320
01:08:20,736 --> 01:08:23,636
I have some on my side, too.

1321
01:08:23,636 --> 01:08:25,216
There are two.

1322
01:08:25,216 --> 01:08:27,606
I was upset.

1323
01:08:27,606 --> 01:08:30,326
We had such a great conversation,

1324
01:08:30,326 --> 01:08:33,516
but it ended up the same way again.

1325
01:08:33,516 --> 01:08:35,896
It didn't last that many hours.

1326
01:08:35,896 --> 01:08:41,016
That's when I first realized that

1327
01:08:41,016 --> 01:08:44,576
he might not have felt the same spark.

1328
01:08:44,576 --> 01:08:46,656
She must be upset.

1329
01:08:47,936 --> 01:08:53,066
I feel like we're getting to know
each other better today.

1330
01:08:53,066 --> 01:08:54,626
[Nodding]

1331
01:08:54,626 --> 01:08:59,466
And we don't often get to have 1:1 talks.

1332
01:08:59,466 --> 01:09:01,346
[Glancing]

1333
01:09:01,346 --> 01:09:04,126
She keeps smiling.

1334
01:09:04,126 --> 01:09:08,136
He's not interested in me?

1335
01:09:08,136 --> 01:09:11,076
He's not that interested in me.

1336
01:09:11,076 --> 01:09:14,536
He wasn't drawing a line with me,

1337
01:09:15,446 --> 01:09:19,606
but I felt like he was leaning toward her.

1338
01:09:19,606 --> 01:09:21,506
Right. It's noticeable.

1339
01:09:21,506 --> 01:09:24,096
Of course, I was bothered by it.

1340
01:09:25,086 --> 01:09:27,546
- Wow.
- How generous.

1341
01:09:28,436 --> 01:09:29,956
You should have some of that.

1342
01:09:29,956 --> 01:09:31,356
Would this be okay?

1343
01:09:31,356 --> 01:09:34,166
I think so. Probably.

1344
01:09:34,986 --> 01:09:37,306
Have some. Have some.

1345
01:09:37,306 --> 01:09:40,716
[Grabbing the tongs right away]

1346
01:09:43,086 --> 01:09:46,426
- Thank you.
- I think I can do it.

1347
01:09:46,426 --> 01:09:49,866
[Seong Min is giving everyone lobster meat]

1348
01:09:49,866 --> 01:09:53,886
You're too far away. This is a meaty part.

1349
01:09:53,886 --> 01:09:56,356
You seem so caring.

1350
01:09:56,356 --> 01:09:58,466
- You're so caring.
- I'm just social.

1351
01:09:58,466 --> 01:10:00,856
You're so caring.

1352
01:10:00,856 --> 01:10:04,066
I wanted to give her the meaty part.

1353
01:10:04,066 --> 01:10:06,766
- What?
- Yu Gyeong.

1354
01:10:09,176 --> 01:10:11,066
You want nabe at home?

1355
01:10:11,066 --> 01:10:12,236
[Nodding]

1356
01:10:12,236 --> 01:10:14,216
Nabe for the second round?

1357
01:10:14,216 --> 01:10:17,466
- We have a meal kit?
- Gosh.

1358
01:10:18,006 --> 01:10:20,616
[Hangover preventative]

1359
01:10:20,616 --> 01:10:22,226
Does it actually work?

1360
01:10:22,226 --> 01:10:23,726
It works when you drink a little.

1361
01:10:23,726 --> 01:10:25,906
- It doesn't if you drink too much.
- You can't help that.

1362
01:10:25,906 --> 01:10:28,206
I've never found it effective.

1363
01:10:28,206 --> 01:10:30,466
You must drink too much.

1364
01:10:30,466 --> 01:10:32,646
I see. It was my fault.

1365
01:10:32,646 --> 01:10:36,366
I'll see if it worked tomorrow.

1366
01:10:37,536 --> 01:10:41,236
- Should we drink the last glass?
- Sounds good.

1367
01:10:41,236 --> 01:10:42,426
[Clank]

1368
01:10:44,976 --> 01:10:46,786
What percentage are you at?

1369
01:10:48,346 --> 01:10:49,776
What percentage?

1370
01:10:49,776 --> 01:10:51,206
10%?

1371
01:10:51,206 --> 01:10:52,896
- 10%?
- 10% drunk?

1372
01:10:52,896 --> 01:10:55,106
- I'm about the same.
- Really?

1373
01:10:55,106 --> 01:10:56,836
It's just right.

1374
01:10:56,836 --> 01:10:59,546
[Feelings are getting
more complicated tonight]

1375
01:10:59,546 --> 01:11:02,916
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for the meal.

1376
01:11:02,916 --> 01:11:05,326
[Yeongjongdo's evening is coming to an end]

1377
01:11:06,366 --> 01:11:08,976
- Too fast.
- This is like an F1 race.

1378
01:11:08,976 --> 01:11:12,336
When we go to a sauna,
we start with a warm bath.

1379
01:11:12,336 --> 01:11:15,996
- This is the hot bath.
- They're jumping from hot and cold.

1380
01:11:15,996 --> 01:11:17,116
[Chaotic]

1381
01:11:17,116 --> 01:11:19,996
We have some strong personalities.

1382
01:11:19,996 --> 01:11:22,136
- They all do.
- They really do.

1383
01:11:22,136 --> 01:11:25,656
Except for Jun Hyeon,
everyone is perfectly decided.

1384
01:11:25,656 --> 01:11:29,656
I'm glad that Wu Yeol
only talked to Gyu Ri today.

1385
01:11:29,656 --> 01:11:32,226
Yu Gyeong detected it quickly, too.

1386
01:11:32,226 --> 01:11:33,956
I'm happy about that.

1387
01:11:33,956 --> 01:11:35,486
He was only looking at Gyu Ri.

1388
01:11:35,486 --> 01:11:38,356
If he got up to take her
to the convenience store,

1389
01:11:38,356 --> 01:11:40,596
I would've got up and gone home, too.

1390
01:11:40,596 --> 01:11:43,516
- I'm serious.
- Really?

1391
01:11:43,516 --> 01:11:48,526
Now that Wu Yeol showed that
he's not interested in her,

1392
01:11:48,526 --> 01:11:54,846
Yu Gyeong could fall for Seong Min
instead. It's perfect timing.

1393
01:11:54,846 --> 01:11:57,726
She's probably attracted to him,

1394
01:11:57,726 --> 01:11:59,636
- but she could be grateful.
- Really?

1395
01:11:59,636 --> 01:12:03,616
She knows he's a good person.

1396
01:12:03,616 --> 01:12:05,156
She just feels a bit sad now.

1397
01:12:05,156 --> 01:12:08,826
- Because she's not attracted to him?
- Exactly.

1398
01:12:08,826 --> 01:12:10,066
He's just a good oppa.

1399
01:12:10,066 --> 01:12:13,236
Eana, if you were in Yu Gyeong's shoes,

1400
01:12:13,236 --> 01:12:17,036
would you switch to someone else,
give up, or push further?

1401
01:12:17,036 --> 01:12:20,846
I'd go even crazier. But I wouldn't push
further because of that.

1402
01:12:20,846 --> 01:12:24,426
I'd hang in there, but my feelings
would grow even more.

1403
01:12:24,426 --> 01:12:27,536
Seong Min was the only person who helped her.

1404
01:12:27,536 --> 01:12:29,586
I think I'd get confused by that.

1405
01:12:29,586 --> 01:12:31,366
- Focus on someone else?
- Yes.

1406
01:12:31,366 --> 01:12:35,656
What about Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri
do you think bothered her the most?

1407
01:12:35,656 --> 01:12:36,886
There was the lip balm.

1408
01:12:36,886 --> 01:12:39,646
"We didn't listen to music.

1409
01:12:39,646 --> 01:12:41,776
There was no gap in audio."

1410
01:12:41,776 --> 01:12:45,516
She must've blamed herself because

1411
01:12:45,516 --> 01:12:49,896
she's been ahead of the other women so far.

1412
01:12:49,896 --> 01:12:52,306
She's never experienced this herself.

1413
01:12:52,306 --> 01:12:55,236
Right. It's been like that even this morning.

1414
01:12:55,236 --> 01:13:01,286
Don't you think her getting sick
was partly due to stress?

1415
01:13:01,286 --> 01:13:02,556
She got better pretty quickly.

1416
01:13:02,556 --> 01:13:04,616
- It was from stress.
- Seems that way, right?

1417
01:13:04,616 --> 01:13:09,316
He kept asking one person if she was drunk.

1418
01:13:09,316 --> 01:13:11,936
I think that was a strong signal.

1419
01:13:11,936 --> 01:13:14,966
If someone you don't like gets drunk,
you say, "Sang Min, go home."

1420
01:13:14,966 --> 01:13:16,356
Right.

1421
01:13:17,706 --> 01:13:20,436
"Oppa, you're drunk." You decide that he is.

1422
01:13:20,436 --> 01:13:21,966
You don't ask them.

1423
01:13:21,966 --> 01:13:26,426
Wu Yeol said the most obvious thing
the way men express their feelings.

1424
01:13:26,426 --> 01:13:29,076
"I want to see you drunk.
I want to see you buzzed."

1425
01:13:29,076 --> 01:13:32,726
- That's going too far.
- That means he likes her a lot.

1426
01:13:32,726 --> 01:13:35,936
When she said she was 0% drunk,

1427
01:13:35,936 --> 01:13:39,236
he seemed disappointed, too.
That's flirting, too.

1428
01:13:39,236 --> 01:13:41,516
It was like, "I wanted you to be drunk."

1429
01:13:41,516 --> 01:13:43,996
They just seemed like a couple flirting.

1430
01:13:43,996 --> 01:13:48,556
Seong Min was different than
when he chatted with Min Ju.

1431
01:13:48,556 --> 01:13:51,146
I didn't know he was so good at flirting.

1432
01:13:51,146 --> 01:13:52,996
He gave her the Beauty Digestive.

1433
01:13:52,996 --> 01:13:55,026
You saw Min Ju's face, right?

1434
01:13:55,026 --> 01:13:59,556
Yu Gyeong thought it was a funny story,

1435
01:13:59,556 --> 01:14:02,866
but Min Ju was like, "What?"

1436
01:14:02,866 --> 01:14:05,836
It breaks my heart a bit. It does.

1437
01:14:05,836 --> 01:14:08,786
I got a sense that Min Ju is strong, too.

1438
01:14:08,786 --> 01:14:11,036
Yu Gyeong told that story calmly,

1439
01:14:11,036 --> 01:14:14,386
but Min Ju expressed
her hurt feelings directly.

1440
01:14:14,386 --> 01:14:15,576
Right, right.

1441
01:14:15,576 --> 01:14:20,426
If I witnessed my crush showing
interest in someone else,

1442
01:14:20,426 --> 01:14:22,936
I'm like, "Goodbye."

1443
01:14:22,936 --> 01:14:25,816
- But they'll live a month together.
- That's the problem.

1444
01:14:25,816 --> 01:14:27,706
Eat breakfast and dinner in the same house.

1445
01:14:27,706 --> 01:14:30,036
- That sucks.
- That's the problem.

1446
01:14:30,036 --> 01:14:31,986
They have 27 days to go.

1447
01:14:31,986 --> 01:14:34,936
Twenty-seven days? What a nightmare.

1448
01:14:34,936 --> 01:14:39,046
- They can't say, "Goodbye."
- That's a tough place to be.

1449
01:14:39,046 --> 01:14:41,496
[Back in Seoul]

1450
01:14:42,006 --> 01:14:45,726
Gyu Ri is sure that a female
game changer moved in.

1451
01:14:45,726 --> 01:14:48,936
She's 200% sure about it.

1452
01:14:48,936 --> 01:14:50,536
You're happy. You're happy.

1453
01:14:50,536 --> 01:14:53,826
It won't happen since you're so sure.

1454
01:14:53,826 --> 01:14:55,236
A female game-changer?

1455
01:14:55,236 --> 01:14:57,486
When will the female game-changer come?

1456
01:14:57,486 --> 01:14:59,496
What if she's there when we get home?

1457
01:14:59,496 --> 01:15:01,576
But since we...

1458
01:15:01,576 --> 01:15:04,386
Since we could see it happening...

1459
01:15:06,256 --> 01:15:08,106
Are you nervous?

1460
01:15:08,106 --> 01:15:08,976
[Shaking head]

1461
01:15:08,976 --> 01:15:11,726
No? Are you confident?

1462
01:15:11,726 --> 01:15:13,106
[Nodding]

1463
01:15:13,106 --> 01:15:15,156
She's confident.

1464
01:15:16,156 --> 01:15:17,476
That can't be.

1465
01:15:17,476 --> 01:15:19,966
I'm excited. I'll open the door first.

1466
01:15:19,966 --> 01:15:21,296
[Smiling]

1467
01:15:22,836 --> 01:15:24,746
Be careful. Don't slip.

1468
01:15:24,746 --> 01:15:27,706
[Arriving at Signal House with excitement]

1469
01:15:27,706 --> 01:15:29,226
Hello.

1470
01:15:29,226 --> 01:15:30,896
I don't think she's here yet.

1471
01:15:30,896 --> 01:15:32,666
[What would be waiting for them?]

1472
01:15:33,666 --> 01:15:35,756
Did I jump the gun?

1473
01:15:36,896 --> 01:15:38,226
My hunch was...

1474
01:15:38,226 --> 01:15:40,416
Unni.

1475
01:15:42,766 --> 01:15:44,836
She might be in our room.

1476
01:15:44,836 --> 01:15:48,936
- It'd be funny if she's hiding somewhere.
- That'd be such a prank.

1477
01:15:50,236 --> 01:15:51,936
My gosh.

1478
01:15:53,556 --> 01:15:54,736
What?

1479
01:15:54,736 --> 01:15:56,396
- What's this?
- Is she there?

1480
01:15:56,396 --> 01:16:00,256
- What?
- I found something else.

1481
01:16:00,256 --> 01:16:03,666
- What's this?
- What's something else?

1482
01:16:03,666 --> 01:16:06,386
What's this? There's a lot of stuff.

1483
01:16:06,386 --> 01:16:07,966
What is it?

1484
01:16:07,966 --> 01:16:09,156
Wow.

1485
01:16:09,156 --> 01:16:10,596
Hold on.

1486
01:16:11,366 --> 01:16:13,896
- Whoa.
- Crazy.

1487
01:16:13,896 --> 01:16:15,006
Books.

1488
01:16:15,006 --> 01:16:17,376
- Books?
- Slam Dunk.

1489
01:16:17,376 --> 01:16:20,346
I knew there would be something new.

1490
01:16:21,336 --> 01:16:23,976
The top is men's and the bottom is women's.

1491
01:16:23,976 --> 01:16:27,536
Are they the books they like?

1492
01:16:27,536 --> 01:16:31,896
I see what it is. The books.

1493
01:16:33,866 --> 01:16:36,546
[Three weeks before moving in]

1494
01:16:36,546 --> 01:16:38,326
[They were asked what their favorite book is]

1495
01:16:38,326 --> 01:16:40,196
Favorite book?

1496
01:16:44,736 --> 01:16:48,676
[The book that made them who they are]

1497
01:16:51,226 --> 01:16:57,606
[They found their favorite
quote from the book, too]

1498
01:17:12,396 --> 01:17:16,956
It's memorable to me since
it's the first book I enjoyed.

1499
01:17:16,956 --> 01:17:20,546
It's a musical I love.

1500
01:17:20,546 --> 01:17:23,206
So, I read the book, too.

1501
01:17:23,906 --> 01:17:26,506
It's a love story.

1502
01:17:26,506 --> 01:17:29,316
"In a universe of ambiguity,

1503
01:17:29,316 --> 01:17:32,926
this kind of certainty comes only once,

1504
01:17:32,926 --> 01:17:36,606
and never again, no matter how
many lifetimes you live."

1505
01:17:36,606 --> 01:17:38,936
You can love someone that deeply.

1506
01:17:38,936 --> 01:17:44,346
When I read books like this
expressing these feelings,

1507
01:17:45,646 --> 01:17:47,526
it gets me curious.

1508
01:17:47,526 --> 01:17:51,316
What can I do to feel this way?

1509
01:17:51,316 --> 01:17:53,306
That's so romantic.

1510
01:17:53,306 --> 01:17:56,666
I find the author's quote so relatable, too.

1511
01:17:56,666 --> 01:17:58,906
"The world is full of doubts and danger,

1512
01:17:58,906 --> 01:18:01,366
but humankind has overcome hard times.

1513
01:18:01,366 --> 01:18:04,716
So, let's not reserve ourselves
when it comes to love.

1514
01:18:04,716 --> 01:18:07,936
Right now is the best moment to be in love."

1515
01:18:07,936 --> 01:18:13,956
We need to love each other
to create a good society.

1516
01:18:13,956 --> 01:18:15,736
It'd be nice if everyone were happy.

1517
01:18:15,736 --> 01:18:18,686
That expresses my value so well.

1518
01:18:18,686 --> 01:18:20,456
That's why it's my favorite book.

1519
01:18:20,456 --> 01:18:23,676
- It shows how nice they are.
- Underlining the text.

1520
01:18:23,676 --> 01:18:28,036
The protagonist starts
playing basketball for a girl.

1521
01:18:28,036 --> 01:18:31,276
His crush asked him if he likes basketball.

1522
01:18:31,276 --> 01:18:33,076
So, he starts playing basketball.

1523
01:18:33,076 --> 01:18:34,456
"Slam Dunk."

1524
01:18:34,456 --> 01:18:38,306
Don't you think that's cool?

1525
01:18:38,306 --> 01:18:41,296
He was terrible, but because of his crush,

1526
01:18:41,296 --> 01:18:43,476
he grows to love basketball.

1527
01:18:43,476 --> 01:18:45,036
He's pure. He's pure.

1528
01:18:45,036 --> 01:18:49,656
You can love someone when you love yourself.

1529
01:18:49,656 --> 01:18:55,676
The book aligns with my views
on life and relationships.

1530
01:18:55,676 --> 01:18:58,676
That's why it's my favorite book.

1531
01:18:58,676 --> 01:19:03,986
When you love someone,
you need to maintain your own self,

1532
01:19:03,986 --> 01:19:06,906
but you also need
to become one with the other.

