I can't share too much detail.

1790
01:34:31,706 --> 01:34:34,046
Ask me. I'll tell you, too.

1791
01:34:34,046 --> 01:34:35,746
Don't you have any questions for me?

1792
01:34:35,746 --> 01:34:39,886
- I feel a little cautious to ask.
- Really?

1793
01:34:39,886 --> 01:34:42,946
- I can tell you everything.
- Really?

1794
01:34:45,286 --> 01:34:46,856
I can't read you.

1795
01:34:46,856 --> 01:34:48,426
In what way?

1796
01:34:48,426 --> 01:34:50,906
Your...

1797
01:34:50,906 --> 01:34:52,586
Really?

1798
01:34:54,586 --> 01:34:56,916
Oh, really?

1799
01:34:57,916 --> 01:35:00,716
Yes. Or am I clueless?

1800
01:35:00,716 --> 01:35:02,396
Who is it?

1801
01:35:10,126 --> 01:35:11,556
Seong Min.

1802
01:35:11,556 --> 01:35:13,006
What?

1803
01:35:14,386 --> 01:35:16,396
- Right.
- What do we do?

1804
01:35:16,396 --> 01:35:18,746
But what about what she just said?

1805
01:35:18,746 --> 01:35:21,316
Things got funny just now.

1806
01:35:21,316 --> 01:35:22,796
Seong Min.

1807
01:35:22,796 --> 01:35:24,226
What?

1808
01:35:26,056 --> 01:35:29,496
What are you saying? I'm the most obvious.

1809
01:35:32,626 --> 01:35:35,046
[Closing eyes]

1810
01:35:37,446 --> 01:35:42,286
[The atmosphere suddenly got awkward]

1811
01:35:47,806 --> 01:35:49,396
Is that so?

1812
01:35:51,056 --> 01:35:53,726
He's so fun.

1813
01:35:53,726 --> 01:35:56,096
He's so easy to talk to.

1814
01:35:57,586 --> 01:35:59,836
[Fidgeting]

1815
01:36:02,916 --> 01:36:08,936
I learned something in the car
on the way to Yeongjongdo.

1816
01:36:08,936 --> 01:36:14,816
You can't rush things. You can't be hasty.

1817
01:36:14,816 --> 01:36:18,306
- Did you realize that on your own?
- While talking.

1818
01:36:18,306 --> 01:36:23,296
I decided not to,
but I couldn't control myself.

1819
01:36:23,296 --> 01:36:25,766
She felt it herself.

1820
01:36:25,766 --> 01:36:29,606
But while talking to him today,

1821
01:36:29,606 --> 01:36:32,716
he said he observes people for a long time.

1822
01:36:32,716 --> 01:36:37,076
When he talked about himself,

1823
01:36:37,076 --> 01:36:41,706
I thought I should be like him, too.

1824
01:36:42,626 --> 01:36:45,556
And to be honest,

1825
01:36:48,286 --> 01:36:52,176
that was one of the biggest reasons.

1826
01:36:52,176 --> 01:36:54,476
And the other reason is...

1827
01:36:56,326 --> 01:36:58,786
while we were eating...

1828
01:36:58,786 --> 01:37:00,866
- I'll go real quick.
- Where?

1829
01:37:00,866 --> 01:37:05,746
[Seong Min was helping Yu Gyeong
in front of her]

1830
01:37:05,746 --> 01:37:09,516
During dinner, I was a bit...

1831
01:37:10,836 --> 01:37:12,476
I was a bit...

1832
01:37:12,476 --> 01:37:15,466
What a headache for Yu Gyeong.

1833
01:37:15,466 --> 01:37:18,896
I just have feelings for Seong Min

1834
01:37:18,896 --> 01:37:23,146
and I want to get to know the others, too.

1835
01:37:24,806 --> 01:37:29,936
I must be learning about love.

1836
01:37:29,936 --> 01:37:33,536
- What a headache.
- This is crazy.

1837
01:37:37,416 --> 01:37:39,646
We're hearing from the men now.

1838
01:37:39,646 --> 01:37:41,656
Each day, it feels like...

1839
01:37:43,046 --> 01:37:44,956
I know.

1840
01:37:46,106 --> 01:37:51,076
I sometimes want to run away to work.

1841
01:37:51,076 --> 01:37:55,126
I have too much to think about here.

1842
01:37:55,126 --> 01:37:57,736
I might need to make a decision soon.

1843
01:37:57,736 --> 01:38:02,126
Isn't it natural to change
feelings at this point?

1844
01:38:02,126 --> 01:38:06,066
- Right. At this point.
- It's still Day 3.

1845
01:38:06,066 --> 01:38:08,806
If I keep talking to them,

1846
01:38:09,756 --> 01:38:15,006
I might change my mind or become more sure.

1847
01:38:15,006 --> 01:38:17,266
I think it'll get even harder.

1848
01:38:19,596 --> 01:38:23,876
[Who should they express their feelings to?]

1849
01:38:25,976 --> 01:38:28,336
[Day 3 evening is much tougher]

1850
01:38:28,336 --> 01:38:30,916
- I feel bad for Yu Gyeong today.
- Her head hurts.

1851
01:38:30,916 --> 01:38:33,436
It was a long day for her.

1852
01:38:38,796 --> 01:38:42,476
I'm so curious about Min Ju's next move.

1853
01:38:46,766 --> 01:38:54,196
[Where are their hearts headed now?]

1854
01:38:57,266 --> 01:39:02,306
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

1855
01:39:02,306 --> 01:39:06,456
[Predict the seven people's
love lines based on clues!]

1856
01:39:06,456 --> 01:39:08,836
- Wow.
- This is so...

1857
01:39:08,836 --> 01:39:10,926
It's harder than usual today.

1858
01:39:10,926 --> 01:39:13,806
Let's start with the easy ones.
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.

1859
01:39:13,806 --> 01:39:16,006
Park Wu Yeol and Jeong Gyu Ri.

1860
01:39:16,006 --> 01:39:18,936
Gyu Ri.

1861
01:39:18,936 --> 01:39:21,896
- You can draw Gyu Ri's, too.
- We're sure about these two.

1862
01:39:21,896 --> 01:39:23,816
Yes. Totally sure.

1863
01:39:23,816 --> 01:39:25,446
[Jeong Gyu Ri and Park Wu Yeol]

1864
01:39:25,446 --> 01:39:29,176
- Jeong Gyu Ri and Park Wu Yeol.
- It was all about them.

1865
01:39:29,176 --> 01:39:32,426
And Kim Seong Min
definitely chooses Yu Gyeong.

1866
01:39:32,426 --> 01:39:34,986
- The Beauty Digestive.
- It's getting clear, right?

1867
01:39:34,986 --> 01:39:37,796
[Choosing Kang Yu Gyeong for Kim Seong Min]

1868
01:39:37,796 --> 01:39:39,976
Jeong Jun Hyeon probably
chooses Yu Gyeong, too.

1869
01:39:39,976 --> 01:39:43,316
He wasn't showing interest
in anyone else, either.

1870
01:39:43,316 --> 01:39:45,986
He's becoming more likable.

1871
01:39:45,986 --> 01:39:48,886
Jun Hyeon chooses Yu Gyeong.

1872
01:39:48,886 --> 01:39:52,936
Yu Gyeong definitely will
choose Seong Min, right?

1873
01:39:52,936 --> 01:39:55,336
- I think so, too.
- We know that for sure.

1874
01:39:55,336 --> 01:39:58,886
- I'm nervous about agreeing with Roy.
- I'm feeling confident today.

1875
01:39:58,886 --> 01:40:00,606
That's actually one of the easiest ones.

1876
01:40:00,606 --> 01:40:02,866
This one's easy. Yu Gyeong, Seong Min.

1877
01:40:02,866 --> 01:40:05,726
She won't avoid him because of Min Ju?

1878
01:40:05,726 --> 01:40:10,016
No feelings for Jun Hyeon
after driving together?

1879
01:40:10,016 --> 01:40:10,936
Wait, hold on.

1880
01:40:10,936 --> 01:40:15,176
I thought she might've panicked
after talking to Min Ju.

1881
01:40:15,176 --> 01:40:17,526
She could say,
"Jun Hyeon, thank you for today."

1882
01:40:17,526 --> 01:40:22,356
I think she'll message Seong Min
for caring for her today,

1883
01:40:22,356 --> 01:40:25,246
getting her medicine, and thank him.

1884
01:40:25,246 --> 01:40:29,566
Driving versus a convenience store.
Convenience store wins.

1885
01:40:29,566 --> 01:40:30,756
Totally.

1886
01:40:30,756 --> 01:40:33,606
She'll choose Seong Min, who treated her.

1887
01:40:33,606 --> 01:40:35,326
Our doctor.

1888
01:40:35,326 --> 01:40:38,106
I think Min Ju chooses Seong Min.

1889
01:40:38,106 --> 01:40:41,126
My note says, "Min Ju chooses Seo Won."

1890
01:40:41,126 --> 01:40:42,456
Min Ju chooses Seo Won?

1891
01:40:42,456 --> 01:40:46,906
I drew an angry face next to Min Ju.

1892
01:40:46,906 --> 01:40:48,986
She'll choose Seo Won out of anger?

1893
01:40:48,986 --> 01:40:52,196
Not that she clearly chooses Seo Won,

1894
01:40:52,196 --> 01:40:54,776
it's more like not choosing Seong Min.

1895
01:40:54,776 --> 01:40:56,876
I think it's still Seong Min.

1896
01:40:56,876 --> 01:40:58,396
I agree. I agree.

1897
01:40:58,396 --> 01:41:01,046
So many serendipitous things.
The book, for instance.

1898
01:41:01,046 --> 01:41:04,606
Seong Min had the biggest impact today.

1899
01:41:04,606 --> 01:41:06,136
[Torn]

1900
01:41:06,136 --> 01:41:08,676
I'm 100% sure.

1901
01:41:08,676 --> 01:41:10,636
- Who is it?
- I'm certain...

1902
01:41:10,636 --> 01:41:12,496
Certain?

1903
01:41:12,496 --> 01:41:14,576
- She'll text Seong Min.
- Seong Min?

1904
01:41:14,576 --> 01:41:17,426
We're choosing Seo Won, then.

1905
01:41:17,426 --> 01:41:18,676
[LOL]

1906
01:41:18,676 --> 01:41:21,196
- And think about this.
- I'm 100% sure.

1907
01:41:21,196 --> 01:41:24,496
Min Ju said you can't be hasty.

1908
01:41:24,496 --> 01:41:27,386
You can't rush things. You can't be hasty.

1909
01:41:27,386 --> 01:41:29,216
Right.

1910
01:41:30,216 --> 01:41:32,136
- You're right.
- She said that.

1911
01:41:32,136 --> 01:41:34,986
Rip your thin ears, please.

1912
01:41:34,986 --> 01:41:37,086
They're so floppy. I'm about to fly.

1913
01:41:37,086 --> 01:41:38,236
[He's silly]

1914
01:41:38,236 --> 01:41:41,996
Think about this. They don't
necessarily text someone

1915
01:41:41,996 --> 01:41:44,036
they want to go out with the next day.

1916
01:41:44,036 --> 01:41:47,366
It's based on what happened that day.

1917
01:41:47,366 --> 01:41:49,536
They don't say, "Let's give it a shot."

1918
01:41:49,536 --> 01:41:52,586
- Let's choose Seong Min for Min Ju.
- Go with the majority.

1919
01:41:52,586 --> 01:41:55,986
Min Ju chooses Seong Min.

1920
01:41:55,986 --> 01:41:58,446
If we're wrong about this,

1921
01:41:58,446 --> 01:42:00,256
we can't speak next week.

1922
01:42:00,256 --> 01:42:01,896
You can't speak for five minutes.

1923
01:42:01,896 --> 01:42:04,086
[I like that]

1924
01:42:04,086 --> 01:42:06,866
- Kim Seo Won.
- That's a tough one.

1925
01:42:06,866 --> 01:42:09,586
Could you read him today?

1926
01:42:09,586 --> 01:42:12,126
He chose Min Ju last week.

1927
01:42:12,126 --> 01:42:14,476
- I think Seo Won chooses Min Ju.
- Right?

1928
01:42:14,476 --> 01:42:19,186
He kept talking to her over dinner.

1929
01:42:19,186 --> 01:42:22,276
I think Seo Won chooses Yu Gyeong,
but we'll go with Min Ju.

1930
01:42:22,276 --> 01:42:23,996
What? Why?

1931
01:42:23,996 --> 01:42:25,896
He went near Yu Gyeong.

1932
01:42:25,896 --> 01:42:28,486
He did sit next to her at the cafe.

1933
01:42:28,486 --> 01:42:33,226
His initial feelings
for Yu Gyeong are still there.

1934
01:42:33,226 --> 01:42:36,126
He joined them late after work today.

1935
01:42:36,126 --> 01:42:41,746
Did his feelings for Yu Gyeong
change while he was gone?

1936
01:42:41,746 --> 01:42:43,736
Yu Gyeong. I think it's Yu Gyeong.

1937
01:42:43,736 --> 01:42:45,486
He texted Min Ju because
they had cooked together.

1938
01:42:45,486 --> 01:42:47,636
So, it was nothing more than that.

1939
01:42:47,636 --> 01:42:51,296
- Seo Won chooses Yu Gyeong.
- Could that be right?

1940
01:42:51,296 --> 01:42:54,196
- Okay. Let's go.
- Seo Won and Yu Gyeong?

1941
01:42:55,826 --> 01:42:57,186
I wonder what they will say.

1942
01:42:57,186 --> 01:42:59,096
[Confusion is growing deeper
on the night of Day 3]

1943
01:43:02,476 --> 01:43:11,166
[I want to prioritize feelings]

1944
01:43:11,166 --> 01:43:13,716
[Thinking]

1945
01:43:14,256 --> 01:43:18,436
[Seong Min thinks Sleepy Bear is Min Ju]

1946
01:43:19,566 --> 01:43:22,696
Huh? Who is it?

1947
01:43:23,966 --> 01:43:25,006
[Sleepy Bear]

1948
01:43:25,006 --> 01:43:28,506
Sleepy Bear says, "Thanks for
the lint roller. It was useful."

1949
01:43:28,506 --> 01:43:33,736
[Sleepy Bear]

1950
01:43:33,736 --> 01:43:36,036
- Huh?
- You scared me.

1951
01:43:36,036 --> 01:43:37,006
It was Park Wu Yeol.

1952
01:43:37,006 --> 01:43:39,236
- Park Wu Yeol?
- Seriously?

1953
01:43:39,236 --> 01:43:43,436
It's not "I like you."
It's "Let's get to know each other."

1954
01:43:43,436 --> 01:43:46,856
- I think she just chose randomly.
- But it's too random.

1955
01:43:46,856 --> 01:43:48,896
She'll be back on track soon.

1956
01:43:48,896 --> 01:43:50,926
- Today, she was...
- Is it anger?

1957
01:43:50,926 --> 01:43:54,066
She was a bit hurt, of course.

1958
01:43:54,066 --> 01:43:57,386
She sent a meaningless text since she had to.

1959
01:43:57,386 --> 01:43:58,946
It was just random.

1960
01:43:58,946 --> 01:44:02,636
We were right
about her not picking Seong Min.

1961
01:44:02,636 --> 01:44:05,536
What? Lint roller?

1962
01:44:09,156 --> 01:44:12,266
- This isn't easy.
- It isn't.

1963
01:44:13,306 --> 01:44:14,476
[Dried Sweet Potato]

1964
01:44:14,476 --> 01:44:17,766
"I'm curious what your book is.
Good night. Dried Sweet Potato"

1965
01:44:17,766 --> 01:44:20,076
That's her... Gyu Ri.

1966
01:44:20,076 --> 01:44:24,766
- These two are fixed for now.
- They are.

1967
01:44:26,436 --> 01:44:27,396
[Flopping down]

1968
01:44:27,396 --> 01:44:29,726
It's tricky.

1969
01:44:30,606 --> 01:44:33,326
Do you have a facial mask? A facial mask?

1970
01:44:33,326 --> 01:44:36,046
- Me? I don't.
- Do you want one?

1971
01:44:36,046 --> 01:44:37,536
[Is Wu Yeol getting ready for tomorrow?]

1972
01:44:38,196 --> 01:44:42,076
[Who will they express their feelings to?]

1973
01:44:42,076 --> 01:44:47,766
[Things are getting more difficult
at Signal House tonight]

1974
01:44:49,706 --> 01:44:52,236
- Who is it?
- Seong Min?

1975
01:44:53,766 --> 01:44:54,786
[My Dog, Yellow]

1976
01:44:54,786 --> 01:44:57,766
"It's so fun talking to you."

1977
01:44:57,766 --> 01:44:59,036
- Yellow.
- That's right.

1978
01:44:59,036 --> 01:45:00,826
What a relief. What a relief.

1979
01:45:00,826 --> 01:45:03,656
He cared for her when she was sick.

1980
01:45:07,966 --> 01:45:09,606
Can he not believe it?

1981
01:45:09,606 --> 01:45:12,266
He might not know that it's Yu Gyeong.

1982
01:45:12,266 --> 01:45:15,346
But he's been getting texts from Sleepy Bear.

1983
01:45:15,346 --> 01:45:17,686
He could guess that it's Yu Gyeong.

1984
01:45:17,686 --> 01:45:21,296
[They're waiting
for the men's texts nervously]

1985
01:45:21,296 --> 01:45:23,686
[Buzz]

1986
01:45:25,576 --> 01:45:27,136
[Tired Camel]

1987
01:45:27,136 --> 01:45:29,096
- Really?
- Seo Won texted Min Ju?

1988
01:45:30,506 --> 01:45:35,736
[Tired Camel]

1989
01:45:35,736 --> 01:45:37,966
Geez.

1990
01:45:37,966 --> 01:45:39,866
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

1991
01:45:39,866 --> 01:45:42,726
I wasn't sure about this.

1992
01:45:42,726 --> 01:45:44,836
- He sat next to her for no reason.
- This is so annoying.

1993
01:45:44,836 --> 01:45:46,186
Why Min Ju?

1994
01:45:46,186 --> 01:45:48,146
Did he start liking Min Ju in Episode 2?

1995
01:45:48,146 --> 01:45:49,776
He texted Min Ju in Episode 2.

1996
01:45:49,776 --> 01:45:51,506
But was it out of attraction?

1997
01:45:51,506 --> 01:45:54,076
I think Seo Won hasn't decided yet.

1998
01:45:54,076 --> 01:45:56,206
He hasn't.

1999
01:45:56,206 --> 01:46:00,416
[While they're torn,
the night is growing deeper]

2000
01:46:03,176 --> 01:46:05,806
I was grateful to him.

2001
01:46:05,806 --> 01:46:10,266
[Gratitude for Seong Min]

2002
01:46:10,266 --> 01:46:13,566
[And guilt toward Min Ju]

2003
01:46:14,666 --> 01:46:16,466
[Torn]

2004
01:46:17,086 --> 01:46:20,566
I ran my mouth cluelessly.

2005
01:46:21,876 --> 01:46:28,226
I think waiting for Wu Yeol expectantly...

2006
01:46:28,226 --> 01:46:31,156
would be hard on me.

2007
01:46:33,816 --> 01:46:40,046
I just thought he went to her.

2008
01:46:40,046 --> 01:46:45,416
I wanted to see you slightly buzzed.

2009
01:46:46,326 --> 01:46:49,146
Not at all. Not at all.

2010
01:46:50,016 --> 01:46:51,836
[Head down]

2011
01:46:51,836 --> 01:46:55,656
- Yu Gyeong is having a hard time.
- What do we do?

2012
01:46:55,656 --> 01:46:59,016
[She's afraid because she knows she'll
get hurt by having expectations]

2013
01:46:59,016 --> 01:47:01,306
[Buzz]

2014
01:47:05,876 --> 01:47:07,396
[Beluga of the Forest]

2015
01:47:07,396 --> 01:47:09,166
"Don't be sick."

2016
01:47:09,166 --> 01:47:11,046
Beluga.

2017
01:47:11,916 --> 01:47:14,846
So cute. "Don't be sick."

2018
01:47:14,846 --> 01:47:17,206
I like Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong, too.

2019
01:47:17,206 --> 01:47:21,276
[Just waiting for Seong Min
and Wu Yeol's texts]

2020
01:47:25,356 --> 01:47:27,126
[Busy Hamster]

2021
01:47:27,126 --> 01:47:29,926
I got a text from Hamster.

2022
01:47:29,926 --> 01:47:31,966
It was Hamster.

2023
01:47:32,966 --> 01:47:35,516
And it's Wu Yeol.

2024
01:47:36,636 --> 01:47:39,306
[Smile]

2025
01:47:39,306 --> 01:47:41,466
I couldn't help but smile.

2026
01:47:42,636 --> 01:47:45,176
I felt uncomfortable for some reason.

2027
01:47:45,176 --> 01:47:48,236
But maybe I was mistaken.

2028
01:47:48,236 --> 01:47:53,036
It turned out so well. You improved a lot.

2029
01:47:53,036 --> 01:47:55,746
- This is complimentary.
- Let's eat, Yellow.

2030
01:47:55,746 --> 01:47:58,486
[Flustered]

2031
01:47:59,276 --> 01:48:03,566
[Decided to maintain hope]

2032
01:48:04,436 --> 01:48:07,206
- Right. She's been thinking that.
- But she's wrong.

2033
01:48:07,206 --> 01:48:08,866
- Hamster is Seong Min.
- That's right.

2034
01:48:08,866 --> 01:48:11,366
Gosh, what do we do?

2035
01:48:11,366 --> 01:48:12,766
[The last one is Salt Bread]

2036
01:48:12,766 --> 01:48:15,516
Who will Wu Yeol text?

2037
01:48:15,516 --> 01:48:17,716
Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol.

2038
01:48:22,666 --> 01:48:25,436
[Getting up]

2039
01:48:30,556 --> 01:48:33,276
[Gyu Ri is leaving the room]

2040
01:48:38,256 --> 01:48:39,996
[Her phone is silent]

2041
01:48:39,996 --> 01:48:41,056
She's nervous.

2042
01:48:41,056 --> 01:48:41,826
[Pause]

2043
01:48:48,716 --> 01:48:52,806
[Opening Salt Bread's book]

2044
01:48:52,806 --> 01:48:56,496
- She likes him a lot.
- Yes, she does.

2045
01:48:56,496 --> 01:49:01,086
[Flipping through his book slowly]

2046
01:49:01,666 --> 01:49:07,726
[Who do you wish the book you chose
belonged to?]

2047
01:49:07,726 --> 01:49:15,116
I hope it's Wu Yeol. But...

2048
01:49:16,006 --> 01:49:19,006
But... But...

2049
01:49:21,036 --> 01:49:27,236
I think I'm moving much faster...

2050
01:49:29,466 --> 01:49:34,816
than I thought I would.

2051
01:49:34,816 --> 01:49:38,466
Right. She might be anxious.

2052
01:49:38,466 --> 01:49:48,166
I'm afraid that I won't
be able to control myself.

2053
01:49:48,166 --> 01:49:50,886
That's a scary feeling.

2054
01:49:54,606 --> 01:49:57,966
I'm actually getting nervous.

2055
01:49:57,966 --> 01:50:01,336
Liking someone is a big deal.

2056
01:50:04,186 --> 01:50:07,976
[Where is Gyu Ri's anxiety coming from?]

2057
01:50:09,066 --> 01:50:13,196
It suddenly moved me for some reason.

2058
01:50:14,126 --> 01:50:16,366
Should we go together, then?

2059
01:50:23,976 --> 01:50:28,406
I thought this shouldn't be happening.

2060
01:50:28,406 --> 01:50:32,156
I thought, "I shouldn't do this.
This isn't right."

2061
01:50:35,076 --> 01:50:37,466
[Buzz]

2062
01:50:40,216 --> 01:50:45,076
[Salt Bread: I'm glad we grew closer.
Today was memorable.]

2063
01:50:48,436 --> 01:50:49,746
[Tossing]

2064
01:50:59,226 --> 01:51:03,866
I thought I'd catch myself
feeling anxious often.

2065
01:51:03,866 --> 01:51:08,916
I felt pressured emotionally.

2066
01:51:14,496 --> 01:51:16,156
This is fun.

2067
01:51:18,956 --> 01:51:20,656
This is fun.

2068
01:51:21,956 --> 01:51:25,526
But if I stop getting his texts,

2069
01:51:25,526 --> 01:51:29,976
I'll get so upset. I can see that happening.

2070
01:51:34,756 --> 01:51:45,716
[The flood of emotions is overwhelming]

2071
01:51:46,356 --> 01:51:50,506
She's scared of her feelings right now.

2072
01:51:51,776 --> 01:51:54,696
I always tend to hide my feelings.

2073
01:51:54,696 --> 01:51:59,896
But knowing I'll be facing them was tough.

2074
01:52:03,466 --> 01:52:06,746
[The night before their first official date]

2075
01:52:06,746 --> 01:52:11,516
[The time passes as each person
has their own worries]

2076
01:52:14,706 --> 01:52:19,326
[Salt Bread]

2077
01:52:19,836 --> 01:52:23,706
- In just three days?
- She's scared of her feelings right now.

2078
01:52:23,706 --> 01:52:24,966
Why is she crying?

2079
01:52:24,966 --> 01:52:27,636
- She's scared.
- She likes him too much.

2080
01:52:27,636 --> 01:52:29,646
You don't know how that feels, do you?

2081
01:52:29,646 --> 01:52:31,716
- I know.
- You don't. Of course not.

2082
01:52:31,716 --> 01:52:33,476
You're only scared of ghosts.

2083
01:52:33,476 --> 01:52:36,466
- I'm not scared of ghosts. I beat them.
- He's a former Marine.

2084
01:52:36,466 --> 01:52:38,646
But is it more like...

2085
01:52:38,646 --> 01:52:42,576
she's afraid she'll get hurt again?

2086
01:52:42,576 --> 01:52:43,616
That could be.

2087
01:52:43,616 --> 01:52:46,576
There are feelings you have no control over.

2088
01:52:46,576 --> 01:52:48,316
- Of course.
- Is that it?

2089
01:52:48,316 --> 01:52:53,466
She learned that love can always
change. She's older, too.

2090
01:52:53,466 --> 01:52:58,056
She's the last one
who should be crying today.

2091
01:52:58,056 --> 01:53:00,586
She should be dancing secretly.

2092
01:53:00,586 --> 01:53:02,676
She should be the happiest right now.

2093
01:53:02,676 --> 01:53:05,276
You'd be partying if you were her.

2094
01:53:05,276 --> 01:53:06,616
You'd be dancing like this.

2095
01:53:06,616 --> 01:53:11,246
- You'd be clapping with your feet.
- I'd be screaming.

2096
01:53:11,246 --> 01:53:13,086
It's snowing.

2097
01:53:13,086 --> 01:53:14,896
It's pretty, isn't it? So pretty.

2098
01:53:14,896 --> 01:53:17,956
- Wow, it's so romantic.
- So pretty!

2099
01:53:17,956 --> 01:53:21,286
[As long as I can enjoy
the first snow with you]

2100
01:53:22,076 --> 01:53:26,116
I thought we'd cross paths
if we were meant to be.

2101
01:53:26,996 --> 01:53:29,806
I hope it's destiny.

2102
01:53:29,806 --> 01:53:34,686
Someone chose my book, and I'm sitting here.

2103
01:53:35,616 --> 01:53:38,606
I recognized him from far away.

2104
01:53:38,606 --> 01:53:40,226
Really?

2105
01:53:40,226 --> 01:53:42,726
I couldn't help but smile.

2106
01:53:42,726 --> 01:53:45,076
Who did you think it was?

2107
01:53:45,076 --> 01:53:49,146
I was hoping it'd be you.

2108
01:53:49,146 --> 01:53:51,526
[I couldn't be happier]

2109
01:53:53,046 --> 01:53:54,856
You're loving it.

2110
01:53:55,736 --> 01:53:59,026
I can't maintain a poker face.

2111
01:54:00,566 --> 01:54:02,226
Nervous?

2112
01:54:02,226 --> 01:54:04,266
What do you think?

2113
01:54:04,266 --> 01:54:06,326
You don't know.

2114
01:54:07,296 --> 01:54:10,656
Do you believe in destiny?

2115
01:54:10,656 --> 01:54:13,606
I realized we had something here.

2116
01:54:13,606 --> 01:54:16,106
This is what they call destiny.

2117
01:54:17,996 --> 01:54:20,986
He's someone I'm so interested in.

2118
01:54:21,856 --> 01:54:23,546
I like you.
